title: fruit and nut bread
directions: Cream together well shortening and sugar.
Beat in a small amount of egg substitute at a time.
Beat these three ingredients together until the mixture is light and fluffy.
Add mashed bananas and vanilla flavoring, beating well again.
In a separate bowl, mix together the plain flour, salt and soda.
If you are using self-rising flour, leave out the salt and soda.
Add and beat the flour mixture to the other mixture, a little at a time. After getting these mixed well, blend in dates, nuts and oatmeal.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour cream together.
Add jello; mix well. Fold in mandarin oranges.
Add desired amounts of nuts and marshmallows.
Chill.
Delicious!

title: low-fat chicken in orange sauce
directions: Place chicken on a nonstick baking sheet.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine green pepper and broth mix.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until pepper is tender.
Add tomato sauce, orange juice, pineapple, catsup, soy sauce, mustard and garlic salt.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 25 minutes.
Add chicken and orange sections. Heat; serve over hot rice.

title: delta cream pie
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup nuts and margarine.
Press in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Mix cream cheese, 2/3 of the Cool Whip and 1 cup powdered sugar. Spread over crust.
Mix milk, puddings, vanilla and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Spread over Cool Whip mixture to form 3rd layer. Spread remaining 1/3 of the Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts and grated Hershey bar.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sausage stars
directions: Brown sausage.
Heat oven to 350. Combine sausage, cheeses, dressing, and olives; set aside.
Arrange wonton wrappers in mini muffin pans.
Spray with Pam.
Bake for about 5 minutes.
Place wontons on cookie sheet and fill with sausage mixture.
Reheat for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: grandma's old fashioned beef stew
directions: Brown onion and beef.
Add potatoes, turnip, carrots and celery.
When almost done, add shredded cabbage and Gravy Master.

title: okra patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into patties and fry in oil or bacon drippings.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add balance of the ingredients.
Pour into dish to refrigerate.
Very good for poultry dinners.

title: baked eggs
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the milk and salt.
Pour over the bread cubes.
Then add the meat and sprinkle the cheese over all.
Let this mixture set in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake the next morning for 1 hour at 325°.

title: donut muffins
directions: Combine and beat egg, oil and milk.
Sift in remaining ingredients.
Pour into muffin tins.
(Make 10 large or 14 small muffins.)
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: north carolina tacos
directions: Note: May serve greens on the side.

title: corn pancakes
directions: Mix up a batch of your favorite pancake batter.
Add a can of creamed corn.
Stir it in, just until mixed.
Make pancakes as usual.
Enjoy with butter and syrup.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix.
Shape into small balls.
Brown in skillet.
Drain. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over them.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop scoops of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Mix butter with garlic; brush over biscuits before removing from sheet.

title: fried cheese sticks
directions: Cut cheese into 2 1/2 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch sticks.
Roll cheese sticks in flour to coat.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in bread crumbs, making sure cheese is completely coated with crumbs. Chill for 2 to 4 hours or until coating is set.

title: aunt betty's brownies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
If mixture is too thick, add a little cold water.
A thinner batter is better.
Turn into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: chime chunga's
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender, then shred. Put about one half breast in the middle of each tortilla, sprinkle with 505 green chile sauce, seasonings, and cheese. Fold as burrito and fry in hot oil until brown, turn and brown on other side.

title: perked punch
directions: Pour juice in perk coffee pot.
Put red hots in basket and perk.
Serve hot or cold.
May be reheated.
Serves 15.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Set aside to cool.
In a bowl, beat the eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add cheese, bread and crumble up sausage and add.
Stir well.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: green tomato crisp
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
In a very large bowl, dissolve the lime in the cold water.
Dump the tomatoes into the pickling lime solution, making sure all slices are immersed.
Let stand at room temperature 24 hours.
Drain tomatoes; cover with fresh cold water for 1 hour.
Repeat 3 times, changing water after each hour. Drain.

title: passover(haroses)
directions: Coarsely grate apple and mash thoroughly with nuts and cinnamon.
When mixture is smooth, add wine and mix again.
Add sugar to taste.

title: "hand" salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients except bacon and Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate overnight in a covered container.

title: oatmeal cookies (no bake)
directions: Put oats and peanut butter in large mixing bowl, then in saucepan, boil milk, oleo, sugar and cocoa 1 minute or until it makes a soft ball. Pour hot mixture over oatmeal mixture and mix just enough to melt peanut butter. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper or greased dish.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat together cream cheese, butter and vanilla in small mixing bowl.
Beat
in powdered sugar until blended smooth and of spreading consistency.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: oven-baked chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken in egg and then bread crumbs.
In a 13x9 baking dish, arrange chicken.
Bake uncovered 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour Ragu pasta sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve with hot cooked pasta if desired.
Serves 4.

title: mashed potato and cheese bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, put in greased 12 x 12-inch baking dish, sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine egg yolks, milk and shortening. Stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Cook.

title: cheese roll
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Grate other cheese very fine.
Mix all ingredients together.
(Hands work well!)
Make into small rolls and roll in chili powder.
Chill; keep in refrigerator.

title: dave's oven brisket
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, pour over brisket and marinate for several hours.
Cover lightly with foil and bake at 300° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: radio pie
directions: Place ground chuck in bottom of a Dutch oven or deep casserole dish.
Add sliced onions with salt and pepper.
Add peas and tomatoes.
Top with sliced potatoes and more salt and pepper.
Pour on milk even with top of potatoes.
Bake in oven at 375° for at least 2 hours until potatoes are tender.
A little Mrs. Dash or Italian seasonings are good in this, too!

title: butterscotch nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Blend all ingredients except Cashew Frosting on low speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally; pour into pan.
Bake until pick inserted in center comes out clean, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool. Frost with Cashew Frosting.

title: ratatouille
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into large cubes.
Slice zucchini thickly.
Cut bell pepper into large pieces and coarsely chop the onion.
Cut the tomatoes into large pieces.
Place all ingredients into a 4-quart kettle.
Cover and cook over medium heat.
Stir occasionally until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 10 minutes. Don't overcook!
Serves 8.

title: red cinnamon cucumber sticks
directions: Bring to a boil and let stand over cucumbers overnight.
(May have to boil a while in order to melt red hots.)

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Mix melted margarine, pie filling and undrained pineapple in large baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top (do not mix).
Thinly slice 1 stick of margarine and place over cake mix (close together).
Cover with nuts, if desired.
Bake for 1 hour in a 400° oven.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare apples; set aside.
Put oil in mixing bowl; add sugar and eggs and beat until creamy.
Sift flour and measure; sift again with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add flour mixture a little at a time to creamy mixture; beat well after each addition. When batter becomes stiff, add pecans and apples.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and salt; beat until forms peaks.
Fold in butterscotch chips, nuts and vanilla.
Have oven preheated to 350°.
Put cookie dough on ungreased foil by teaspoonfuls and place in oven.
Turn off oven and forget for at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate-peanut butter clusters
directions: Mix chips in bowl and melt in microwave. Stir. Add peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper until firm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup corn bread dressing for topping.
Microwave onion and carrots approximately 1 minute.
Mix all ingredients. Top with reserved dressing.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: chinese noodle casserole
directions: Mix all the
ingredients
except 1/2 the noodles;
pour in greased 2 quart casserole.
Top with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry cake
directions: 1. Mix ingredients and add 1 c. or more blueberries.
2. Bake at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar and water, bring to a boil, remove and put in walk-in.
Take pineapple juice, grapefruit juice and Kool-Aid and mix 1/3 of sugar and water to one gallon of fruit mixture.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper. Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each oil and butter in a large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Do not cook longer, will be dry. Transfer to serving platter. Add chives or onion, lemon and brandy. Add parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds.
Whisk in remaining broth. Stir until smooth. Add remaining butter and oil.
Pour over chicken. Serve immediately.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Stir together ingredients.
Top with 1 tube of crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Whip cream and set aside in icebox.
In double boiler, melt marshmallows in 1/3 cup milk.
Remove from heat and add Hershey bars and vanilla to mixture and cool.
Add whipped cream and pour into pie crust.
Cool one hour in icebox before serving.
Finely chopped nuts may be added for texture.
Can be frozen.

title: parmesan bubble loaf
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough and cut into 16 pieces.
Dip in melted margarine.
Roll in Parmesan cheese.
Grease bread pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer bread dough pieces in pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake approximately 40 minutes.
Check for browning; may have to cover with foil last 15 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable dijon
directions: Arrange chicken in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl, stir soup, mustard, oregano, pepper and milk until smooth.
Spoon 1 cup over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
In large bowl, combine pasta and vegetables, 1/2 can onions and remaining soup mixture.
Spoon over and around chicken pieces in baking dish; cover.
Bake 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and sauce is bubbling.
Top with tomato wedges and remaining onions.
Bake 3 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Put all ingredients, except beets, in pan and boil 15 minutes. Add beets and boil 5 minutes longer. Then they can be canned.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Put the sliced pineapple in a 3-quart roaster with cherry maraschino cherries in the middle.
Mix cake mix and milk together.
Stir and pour over the pineapple and cherries.
Mix together the water, brown sugar and oil.
Stir and pour over cake mix.
Microwave on High for 12 minutes and then check.
May have to add 1 to 2 minutes more depending on your wattage.
Let set 4 to 5 minutes and then flip over in the cover of the Fresh N Fancy.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Bake cake according to box - cool. Beat shortening well, slowly add flour, slowly add sugar, add vanilla, add milk 1/2 at a time. Beat 10 minutes. Spread on cooled cake and freeze until filling is hard. Mix remaining ingredients until smooth, spread on top of filling.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Add one cup boiling water to Jell-O. Let set awhile. Add juice from pineapple. Mix other ingredients with Jell-O and let sit overnight.

title: peach pickle salad
directions: Bring pickle juice to a boil.
Pour over jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 7-Up and chill until slightly thickened.
Add chopped peach pickles and nuts.
Pour into a slightly oiled mold. Store overnight in refrigerator.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand together.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: bean and beef pie
directions: Brown meat and garlic. Mix soup, 1 cup salsa, meat and rest of ingredients. Stir completely. Put crust in pie plate. Put mixture in crust and top with 2nd crust. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Top with sour cream, salsa and olives, if you choose.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add and dissolve sugar with pineapple juice.
Allow to get syrupy.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: lisa's pralines
directions: Toast pecans at 250° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix together the sugar, butter, marshmallows and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until melted together.
Add pecans; continue cooking, stirring constantly, until mixture will make soft ball when dropped into water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat by hand until holds thick shape.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased waxed paper.

title: anytime cheese ball
directions: Combine sour cream and dry salad dressing.
Mix in chopped onions, ham and mix in softened cream cheese.
Mix well.
Form into a ball and roll in sunflower seeds.
Chill and serve with a cracker variety.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, granulated sugar, shortening, vanilla and eggs. Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: a glass of snow
directions: Place bananas, milk, apple juice ice cubes and vanilla into electric blender.
Whirl in blender on low speed for 10 seconds. Don't overblend.
Pour in glass. Serve with a long spoon, like a teaspoon.

title: cranberry bread(christmas bread)
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add without stirring the beaten egg, shortening, orange juice and hot water.
Combine only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in the orange rind, chopped nuts and cranberries.
Bake at 325° for about an hour.
Cool.
Wrap in aluminum foil and freeze.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: pizza bread
directions: Defrost frozen bread dough on greased cookie sheet for 2 hours.
Spread dough to edges.
Brush with beaten egg.
Layer the meats.
Sprinkle with spices and cheeses.
Roll up tight and brush with beaten egg as you roll.
Seal and place, seam side down. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: In heavy saucepan, cook and stir caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk until melted. Set aside.
Combine cake mix, melted margarine, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Stir until dough holds together.

Press half the mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips, then pour on melted caramel mixture. Crumble reserved dough over caramel layer. Bake an additional 15 to 18 minutes. Cool and cut in bars.
Makes 40 bars.

title: "kids love" banana yogurt pops
directions: Mash bananas; add milk and yogurt.
Blend well (recommend mixer or blender).
Pour into small containers (Tupperware popsicle ones work well).
Makes 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder. Add raisins and nuts to wet ingredients.
Combine with zucchini mix.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: jarret anderson tartar's orange-pineapple salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and orange pieces well.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip and stir in.
Pour Jell-O powder over mixture and stir well in salad bowl.
Refrigerate.
This salad sets fast.

title: oven baked hash browns
directions: Melt 1/4 pound butter in large casserole; coat bottom and sides of dish.
Pour remaining butter over chilled potatoes.
Add water and flour to potatoes and toss mixture.
Add garlic salt, salt and pepper to this mixture according to taste.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over entire surface of casserole.
Place potatoes in casserole and pack down lightly.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: western mac
directions: Brown the meat, celery, peppers and onions until tender.
Stir in the corn, tomato paste and water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add the macaroni and cheese.
Put in a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple glaze
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine and pineapple juice.
Let boil together until thickened.
Pour over the cake while hot.

title: dad's scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes gently.
As potatoes cook, mix together mushroom soup, milk and onion.
Drain potatoes.
Put layer in greased casserole dish, then layer of soup mixture. Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Top with cheese.
Layer again until mixtures are gone.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Place
shortening and sugar in bowl; beat for 1 minute. Stop and scrape bowl; beat an additional minute.
Add eggs and beat again.
Mix
flour,
baking
powder, soda and salt into a separate bowl.
Add
dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix on low speed for 1 minute;
add bananas and nuts.	Mix for 30 seconds. Pour
mixture
into
greased and floured 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake	at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: deep dish apple crumb pie
directions: Place apples in deep dish pie pan. Stir in orange juice.
Mix together sugars, orange rind, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and flour. Cut in butter. Spread over apples. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet in butter.
Drain excess fat. Combine Heinz 57 sauce and water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover. Simmer 40 minutes or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally.
Remove cover and simmer an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Skim excess fat from sauces.
Serve sauce over chicken. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add water, salt, tomato sauce, Spanish rice and kidney beans.
Cook on low for 30 minutes and serve.

title: baked beans(electric  full- serves 75)
directions: Soak beans overnight, covered with water. In morning, put on fresh water and boil about 1 hour. Pour into electric roaster and add sugar, catsup, salt, prepared mustard and bacon. Cover with water. Bake at 375° about 4 hours. May need to add more water from time to time.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil all ingredients, except popped corn, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Put in a large pan and place in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring 4 or 5 times.
Put onto waxed paper.
Let cool completely.
When cool, put into airtight container.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix water with brown sugar.
Mix 1/2 cake mix with all ingredients, except pecans.
Beat until smooth.
Add the other 1/2 of cake.
Mix with pecans until smooth.
Spread mixture on two greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Cool well.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds.
Top with chopped almonds.
Heat at 350° for 15 minutes.
Keep warm to serve.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Chop Oreo cookies in fine pieces.
Place half of cookies in bottom of long cake pan.
Mix instant pudding and milk, set aside. Mix cream cheese and sugar, then add Cool Whip.
Then mix that mixture with your pudding.
Place on top of cookies in pan.
Top with remaining Oreos.

title: broccoli fettucine
directions: Melt butter and saute broccoli on medium heat.
Add salt and minced garlic.
Add pepper.
Cover; do not boil.
Mix cream and half and half.
Cook pasta 10 to 12 minutes in 1/4 teaspoon oil. Rinse in cold water.
Drain completely.
Mix all ingredients.
Add grated Romano cheese and simmer.
Add cornstarch to thicken if desired.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Cook chicken and cut into small pieces.
Cook the macaroni in chicken broth.
Mix the ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Cover with the chicken broth and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: working girl's steak dinner
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in crock-pot on setting 3 (or medium). Go to work.
After you change into comfortable clothes, mix ketchup and cornstarch.
Pour into crock-pot, set on high and cook 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: honey nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 400°.
Grease muffin cups.
Mix together first six ingredients.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to honey mixture, stirring just until flour is moistened. Stir in nuts; fill muffin cups 3/4 full and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: swedish aagkaka(breakfast, egg cake)
directions: Put 2 tablespoons oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan and melt in 450° oven.
In medium bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add the next 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add milk slowly until well mixed. Pour batter over melted oleo in pan and return pan to oven.
Bake at 450°
for 20 minutes until puffy and browned.
Remove from oven.
It will settle.
Serve with the toppings.

title: fish patties
directions: Mix fish, egg, onion and cracker crumbs in a bowl.
Heat the shortening or oil in a skillet.
Spoon fish mixture in skillet, flattening each spoonful to a patty, and brown on both sides.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook beef, pepper, salt, green peppers and onions together until tender.
Drain off all water in meat, then put barbecue sauce and hot sauce into meat mixture.
Cook over low heat.

title: crab cakes
directions: Remove any shell left in crabmeat.
Peel potatoes, cook (boil) and mash.
In bowl, mix first 6 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Make into cakes.
Broil or fry in butter.
Serve as main dish or on roll.

title: bourbon balls
directions: In a large bowl, stir together vanilla wafers, confectioners sugar, pecans, corn syrup, cocoa and bourbon until thoroughly combined.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Pour granulated sugar into a pie plate, then roll bourbon balls in sugar.
Store in an airtight container.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.
Do not freeze.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Line
baking
sheet
with
waxed
paper.
In small bowl, cream butter, 10x sugar, milk and almond extract.
(If mixture is
too soft,
add more sugar.) On a surface lightly sprinkled with 10x sugar, knead mixture into a ball.
Using 1 teaspoon of mixture, shape
into a ball.
Indent with thumb.
Place cherry in indention
and
cover
cherry
with
mixture.
(Leave
stem exposed.) Place on baking sheet.
Cover loosely and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Place the chocolate and shortening in a 2 cup glass measuring cup.
Microwave on Medium 3 to 5 minutes, stirring once a minute until smooth.
Holding cherry stem, dip into chocolate,	cover cherry completely and 1/8 inch up stem. Shake off
excess.
Place
on
waxed paper lined tray.
Repeat using all
the
cherries.
Refrigerate
minutes
to
set. Refrigerate,
covered
if
not
serving
soon.
Makes
dozen candies.

title: mammaw's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni 9 minutes in boiling water.
Drain and pour cold water over.
Put macaroni in buttered casserole dish.
Add oleo, cheese and salt.
Beat eggs and slowly add the hot milk to them. Add the egg and milk mixture to the macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, uncovered.

title: parmesan fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
In a small bowl, mix together the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, basil, oregano and pepper.
Set crumb mixture aside.
Place fish on greased rack of a broiler pan. Brush with lemon juice.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over fish.
Broil 3 to 6 minutes more, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: chiles rellenos(serves 2 people)
directions: Brown 2 to 3 pounds ground beef along with 1 large chopped white onion.
Add all other ingredients to meat along with 2 to 3 cups water in large pot; let simmer for 2 to 4 hours.
Serve over spaghetti (with or without beans), covered with shredded cheese and oyster crackers.
Advisable to have Tums or other antacid on hand as part of dessert.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Put in layers as listed.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir just before serving.

title: broccoli salad supreme
directions: Combine vegetables with seasoned salt in serving bowl; mix well.
Pour desired amount of favorite dressing over salad; toss to coat.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: honey oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream honey, shortening and butter until smooth.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, and add vanilla.
Combine flour mixture to honey mixture; mix thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 16 minutes or until browned.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Brown onion in lard (brown a little).
Add hamburg.
When hamburg is done, add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.

title: stuffed peppers(stuffed peppers are easy to make.)
directions: Wash and slice green peppers in half.
Dish out seeds.
In a large bowl, mix remaining ingredients, except the tomato sauce, then fill pepper shells with meat mixture.
Place in a baking dish and pour tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 8.

title: peanut butter chocolate chips cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, water, margarine, peanut butter and half of cake mix (dry) until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Then add other ingredients.
Beat until mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: banana boat pudding
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding and pie filling mix as directed for pudding on package.
Cover surface of pudding mixture with waxed paper or transparent wrap.
Chill.
Fold in miniature marshmallows and heavy cream, whipped.
Line bottom and sides of 10 x 6-inch baking dish with vanilla wafers.
Pour in half of pudding mixture. Cover with 2 bananas, sliced.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.
Chill.
Garnish with additional marshmallows and banana slices, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In large skillet, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
In large mixing bowl, mix together cooked onion, meat and next 6 ingredients until blended. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until cooked through.

title: chicken salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together carefully.
Do not mash.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Add zucchini, coconut and nuts.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into buttered baking dish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together well. Serve with your favorite fresh fruit slices.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and margarine.
Combine cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk, salt, cumin and chopped, cooked chicken.
Add onions to chicken mixture.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture into flour tortillas near edge; roll up.
Place filled tortilla, seam side down in greased baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream and and 1 cup milk, then pour evenly over all tortillas. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove foil. Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar and Jack cheeses.
Bake 5 minutes more to melt cheeses.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, salt, pepper, onion, sour cream and soup.
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with stuffing.
Line casserole dish with stuffing.
Fill with squash mixture, top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Reserve enough stuffing mix to crumble on top of casserole.

title: crawfish noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles as per package; set aside.
Melt margarine and saute onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Add celery soup and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms, Velveeta cheese, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 2 minutes. Add noodles, crawfish and crab and pour into casserole dish.
Top with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Saute onions in margarine in a pot.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Melt cheese in soup. Add milk and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage for 7 or 8 minutes or until tender; drain. Combine the soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat until the cheese melts.
Combine with cabbage; put in casserole dish.
Put bread crumbs and margarine on top of cabbage.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until heated through, about 20 minutes.

title: pineapple puffs
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all together.
Split cookies and fill.

title: slush
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Makes about 14 cups.
Mix 1/2 cup slush and 1/2 cup Sprite or 7-Up.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Measure oleo in 3-quart pan.
Melt over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is very syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well-coated.
Spread warm mixture in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Using buttered spatula, press firmly into even layer.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in large bowl.
Then add remaining ingredients.
After all is well blended, drop into well-greased muffin tins and bake at 375° until browned.
The dough can be made up and kept in a closed container in the refrigerator for about 2 weeks.
Use as you desire for the meal.

title: christmas cut-outs
directions: Sift
together flour, baking powder and soda in a mixing bowl. Cut
in
butter until mixture looks like cornmeal.
Beat eggs. Add sugar and
vanilla
to eggs and beat well.
Add dash of salt. Combine
egg
mixture
with flour and butter mixture. Chill.
On a lightly
floured
board,
roll
dough
to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut in desired
shapes
and
place
on buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for
6 to 8 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yields: 6 dozen.

title: best beef barbecue
directions: Cut roast in quarters.
Place in greased 5 qt. crock pot. Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour over roast. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Slice apart meat; cook for 30 minutes longer.
Serve on rolls.

title: premium bonbons
directions: Place peanut butter chips, chocolate chips, butter and chocolate in a medium pan and cook over very low heat until melted. Stir frequently.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Stir in cracker crumbs gradually to make a stiff dough.
Roll into large marble-sized balls.
Spread pecan meal on waxed paper; roll each bonbon in meal to coat.
Let stand on waxed paper 30 minutes to set.
Store in airtight container at room temperature or in freezer.
Makes about 50.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugars, gradually.
Cream well.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Stir in creamed mixture, beating until smooth.
Add rolled oats, coconut, raisins, dates and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly. Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 325°.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: best ever rum cake
directions: Before starting, sample rum to check quality.
Good, isn't it. Now proceed.
Select large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure rum is of proper quality, put one level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat with electric mixer, beat 1 cup of butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon thugar and beat again. Meanwhile, make sure rum is still alright.
Try another cup.
Open second cordth if necessary.
Add leggs, 2 cups fried druit and beat until high.
If druit gets stuck in beaters, pry loose with drewscriber.
Sample rum again, checking for tonscisticity.
Next sift 3 cups pepper or salt (really doesn't matter).
Sample rum. Sift 1/2 pint lemon juice.
Fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add 1 tablespoon of brown thugar or whatever color you can find.
Wix mel.
Grease oven.
Turn cake pan to 350°.
Pour mess into boven and ake.
Check rum again and bo to ged.

title: honey crunch cookies
directions: Sift
together	first
3 ingredients; set aside.
Cream butter.
Add
honey
a little at a time.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mixture will appear to separate.
Gradually add dry ingredients; mix until moistened. Fold
in
coconut,	morsels
and
cereal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes
or until
golden
brown.
Remove
cookies to cooling rack.

title: swiss radish salad
directions: In a small jar with tight fitting lid, combine vinegar, mustard, anchovy paste and garlic.
Cover and shake well.
Add oils; cover and shake well again.
Set aside.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Pick over the beans, removing any stones, broken beans or other debris you may find.
Then place them in a heavy stockpot with water to cover and leave them overnight to plump.
When ready to cook, drain the beans and put them back in the stockpot with the quart of cold water, bacon fat and onion.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
If more water is needed, during cooking, add only boiling water.
Otherwise the beans will be tough.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add to well beaten eggs and milk in saucepan.
Cook until thickened.
Add vanilla, coconut and butter.
Cool.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add drained pineapple.
Stir in bread cubes; bake in greased casserole (uncovered) at 350° for 1 hour, until lightly browned.
(May be served hot with main course or cold as dessert.)

title: pistachio pudding freezer pie
directions: Prepare pudding as directed.
Cool for 25 minutes in refrigerator.
Remove pudding from bowl and fold whipped cream into large bowl using a spatula.
Add pudding; mix well.
Place mixture into pie crust.
Top with nuts.
Apply cover over pie and freeze for 2 hours.
Enjoy!

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Can garnish with cherries on top.

title: three bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into greased casserole. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.
Can be frozen.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large pot, combine can of chicken soup, 3 cups water and whole, peeled potato.
After it comes to a boil, add chopped onion, garlic and ditalini macaroni.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add dry chicken noodle soup and carrot.
Cook on simmer for 15 minutes. Take out whole potato and mash in bowl with basil, oil and Parmesan cheese.
Add mixture to soup.
Add kidney beans and simmer for 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: apricot saladeverton, missouri
directions: Mix and pour over salad:

title: gerber's beef stew
directions: Cut beef into 2-inch cubes and brown in the oil with the onions and garlic.
Add the puree, the peeled and sliced tomatoes, paprika and cayenne.
Pour the beer over everything and bake in oven for 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender; 3/4 of an hour before end of cooking time, add potatoes.
Serve with noodles (plain), boiled and strained.
Mix with melted butter and grated cheese.

title: joel's pork chops
directions: Dredge chops in flour, bread crumbs and oregano.
Brown in pan with oil.
Transfer to shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chops.

title: ham salad
directions: Chop ham in blender thoroughly. Blend in remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press potatoes into 9-inch pie plate to form crust.
Drizzle melted butter over and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Toss ham and cheeses together, then place in crust.
Beat milk, eggs and seasoned salt.
Pour over ham and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Great for brunches.
Crust can be prepared night before.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Take 100 pounds dough, roll it out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake for 3 minutes at 18° Fahrenheit.
Take them out and frost them!
Then eat.

title: hearty vegetable chicken soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil.
Add garlic and onion; cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except pasta.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.
Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain and stir into soup.
Heat through. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate mint fudge
directions: In a 2-quart micro-proof bowl, combine 3/4 cup sweetened condensed milk with chocolate chips.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until chips are melted.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread half of the chocolate mixture evenly in the bottom of a foil lined 8-inch square pan.
Place pan in the freezer.
Set remaining mixture aside.
In a 1-quart micro-proof bowl, combine remaining condensed milk with white chocolate.
Microwave on High 1 to 3 minutes, stopping to stir occasionally until melted.
Stir in peppermint extract.
Divide peppermint mixture in half and color half with the red food coloring and half with the green food coloring.
Spread pink mixture on top of chilled chocolate layer and return pan to freezer for 5 minutes.
Remove pan from freezer and spread green mixture on top of pink layer.
Return pan to the freezer to set the layers.
If necessary, melt reserved chocolate mixture again in the microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
Spread on top of peppermint layer and return to the freezer to set.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 64 squares of fudge.

title: crunchy cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage with onions in an airtight bowl.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Mix oil, sugar and seasoning package ingredients and chill.

title: black walnut icing
directions: Mix all ingredients except flavoring in saucepan.
Cook, stir while cooking, until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat, add flavoring and butter.
This will fill a two-layer cake.
Use your favorite cake recipe for the layers.

title: mac & cheese
directions: Boil macaroni; drain and rinse.
In same pan, melt margarine; add flour, pepper, dry mustard and salt.
Add milk gradually while stirring; add cheese in cubes to heat evenly.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon and hamburger.
Add onion; cook until onion is tender.
Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: paper mache
directions: Mix water and flour with wire whisk.
Mixture should be same thickness as heavy cream.
Coat a mold (molded clay or an inflated balloon make a good mold) with one layer of newspaper strips which have been dipped in water.
Dip strips in flour mixture and layer over first layer of strips until mold is well coated.
Let stand until strips on mold are dry and hard.
Paint over the strips if you like.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredient together real well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake until mixture is thick.
Bake in 300° oven for about 45 minute to 1 hour.

title: cabbage plate
directions: Combine vegetables; add sugar, salt and oil; mix.
Add water; cook until just tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
(A colorful winter vegetable dish.)

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add Spring Garden dressing and let stand.

title: whole wheat quick bread
directions: Combine egg, buttermilk, molasses and melted butter.
Stir in dry ingredients that have been mixed together.
Stir in nuts and raisins and spoon batter into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Scatter uncooked rice on bottom of a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Lay chicken, skin side up, on top of rice. Combine mushroom soup and onion soup mix. Pour over chicken. Bake at 325° for about 2 hours. Makes about 6 servings.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg and milk with beater.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.

title: fanny mae fudge
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, milk, butter and vanilla.
Boil 2 minutes.
Turn off heat and add marshmallows.
Stir constantly. Gradually add chips, stirring slowly.
Pour into a buttered 12 x 15-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Slow cook roast for about 6 to 8 hours.
About 1 hour before roast is finished cooking add jar of barbecue sauce.
Continue to cook.
Place barbecue on buns and add desired toppings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together dry cake and pudding mixes with poppy seed. Add water and liquid shortening. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Pour batter into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then invert onto plate. Glaze with a glaze made from powdered sugar, lemon juice and melted butter.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In skillet, mix gelatin, cinnamon, water and salt.
Add margarine.	Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Place sweet potatoes in
an
oiled
or	buttered baking dish. Pour mixture over potatoes.
Cover loosely and cook in moderate oven for 15 minutes
or
until	sweet
potatoes
are
glazed.
Yields four servings, about 235 calories per serving.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix sausage with biscuit mix.
Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Add cheese to sausage mixture and stir to blend.
Make into tiny balls and freeze.
Thaw when ready to bake on ungreased cookie sheet in hot oven at 400°.
Serve hot.
Makes about 100 to 150.

title: mennonite egg bread
directions: Mix egg and milk, adding salt.
Remove crusts from bread; dip in mixture.
Fry quickly in hot fat until a delicate brown, turning.
Spread lightly with butter, sprinkle with sugar and place a spoonful of jelly on each piece.
Serves 4.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange first broccoli, then chicken in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour ingredients 3 through 6 over broccoli and chicken. Over this sprinkle remaining ingredients.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs. Beat well. Add flour and beat thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended. Turn batter into a a greased and floured 13x9 inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Generously grease and flour two loaf pans, or line with waxed paper.

title: tomato beef stew
directions: Cook beef until browned in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook until no longer pink, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Add vegetables and sauce.
Heat to simmering. Cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve with cheese topped garlic bread.

title: hearty german goulash
directions: Mix meat, onions, sauerkraut and paprika.
Place in large casserole or Dutch oven.
Add bouillon.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour. Add cubed potatoes and more broth, if necessary.
Cook 1 more hour.
Remove from oven and stir in sour cream or yogurt.
Makes 10 servings.

title: dilly cottage batter bread
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, yeast, onion, salt and dill weed.
Add cottage cheese, water, egg and honey to flour mixture.
Beat 3 minutes by hand or with electric mixer.
Beat in remaining flour. Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Stir down batter; pour into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Let rise in a warm place until light (30 to 40 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: low-fat greek salad
directions: Boil the unpeeled potatoes in water for 30 minutes. Drain and cool. Peel. Slice into a large bowl. Add onion, parsley, bell pepper and season lightly with salt and pepper.
Fold in mayonnaise and chill.
Line 4 salad plates with shredded lettuce. Place a scoop of potato mixture in center of plate.
Place tomato wedges around edge of salad, then place cucumber strips between tomatoes.
Place beet slice on top of salad.
Scatter green pepper rings, olives, radishes and green onions over all.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Serve with fat-free Italian dressing.

title: zesty cauliflower with cheese
directions: Put cauliflower into 2-quart casserole dish with 2 tablespoons of water.
Cover and microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Drain.

title: sweet french salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Makes approximately 2 2/3 cups.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add the eggs.
Sift the flour and soda together; add to the mixture alternately with the mashed bananas.
Add nuts and vanilla last, mixing all ingredients well. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: meat loaf pizza
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper; put into 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; drain fat.
Spread on sauce, cheese and oregano.
Bake for 10 minute more.
Drain again.
May be topped with chopped onions, green peppers or mushrooms.
Serves 4.

title: sweet & savory pumpkin soup
directions: *Clean out pumpkin seeds and brush inside with butter.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 375 F, let stand until cool enough to handle.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Add onions, sauces and beans.
Stir.
Add most of chips and 3/4 of the cheese.
Stir.
Put in a large casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread sour cream over top.
Cover with remaining chips and cheese.
Return to oven 10 minutes more.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine Russian dressing, soup mix and jam; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place flat out in glass baking dish or pan (pan makes them crispier-don't cook as long).
Follow package directions for baking time.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add dressing.
Spread over cooled crescent "pizza" and top with veggies.

title: chicken with garlic & vegetables
directions: Heat oil and butter in a large skillet over medium high heat. Saute chicken breasts 4 to 5 minutes per side, turning occasionally, until chicken is opaque throughout.
Transfer to a platter and keep warm.
Add carrots to skillet and saute over medium heat 1 minute.
Add leek, bell pepper and garlic and saute another minute.
Stir in tomatoes and any juices from platter. Simmer 2 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve vegetables over chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grinath butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and lemon.
Blend well.
Chill.
Roll and cut into shapes.
Bake at 350°, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk; add cornmeal and cook until thick.
Add salt, baking powder, sugar and butter.
Beat the egg yolks and add to the cornmeal mixture.
Beat the egg whites to a soft peak and fold into batter.
Pour into a well buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake uncovered in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stir-fried vegetables and chicken
directions: Saute chicken in oleo.
Add flour.
Brown it a little.
Add water, then add vegetables and simmer.
Salt and pepper.

title: sheepherder dip
directions: Allow spinach to defrost; drain it thoroughly.
Use paper towels to wring out all the water.
Drain and chop water chestnuts.
Combine all ingredients except the loaf, and mix well. For best flavor, refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: lasagna supreme
directions: Remove sausage from casings or use bulk.
Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and spices.
Add spices liberally to your taste.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours. Cook noodles in boiling water until almost done.
Remove from water and cool on waxed paper or foil for easy handling.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Allow potatoes to thaw completely at room temperature (about 3 hours).
In a saucepan, brown the onion in the first 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Stir in the soups, Pet milk, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir and heat over medium heat until mixture reaches the first hint of a simmer, then pour over potatoes and mix well.
Now mix corn flakes thoroughly with the melted margarine.
Pour potato mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and spread evenly.
Spread corn flake mixture evenly over the potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, about 50 minutes at 350°.
Yield: 12 to 15 servings.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: beef bourguignonne
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, cook half of the meat in 1 tablespoon of the hot oil until meat is browned. Remove meat from pan. Add remaining oil, remaining meat, the chopped onion and garlic. Cook until meat is browned and onion is tender. Stir in Burgundy, beef broth, thyme, marjoram, salt, pepper and bay leaves. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Add the mushrooms, carrots and the pearl onions. Return to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and cook about 30 minutes more or until tender. Discard bay leaves. Combine cold water and flour; stir into meat mixture. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more. Stir in bacon. Serve with noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: cracker jacks(this recipe will delight a child's taste buds.)
directions: In a saucepan, and using a candy thermometer, cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat until mixture hardens. Pour into a greased baking dish, and when cooled, cut into squares.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: *One small can evaporated milk (5 ounces); add water to make 1 cup of milk, plus 1 cup of homogenized milk.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and freeze (freezes great in Schwans ice cream plastic tub).
Set out 4 hours before serving and add 2 liter of 7-Up.

title: duck breast supreme
directions: Wrap each duck breast in a slice of bacon and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Around the holes, add large chunks of celery, onion and apple or potato.
Pour 1 can consomme, water, orange juice and Worcestershire sauce over duck.
Sprinkle each breast with Nature's Seasons and a pat of butter.
Add more liquid if needed to come within 1/2-inch of top of dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Cook 1 hour at 400°, then for 3 hours at 250°.
Take foil off and let brown if desired.
Serve over rice.

title: cool ranch casserole
directions: Place the crushed package of cool ranch Doritos in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Brown the ground beef, medium onion, and green pepper together, and then drain.
Mix together the 2 cans of soup and tomatoes and chilies and add to ground beef mixture.
Add salt and pepper and pour over crushed Doritos.
Sprinkle large bag of cheddar cheese over top of ground beef mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese melts.

title: fried beaver tail
directions: Skin beaver tail; wash and put into a pot of water.
Bring to boil.
Add 2 bay leaves and simmer for 2 hours.
Let cool.
Heat oil in skillet.
Cut tail into slices.
Salt and pepper to taste. Roll in flour and fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Really tastes great.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Beat all together with mixer.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: overnight layered green salad
directions: Shred lettuce into shallow serving dish (about 4-quart size). Top with green onion, celery and water chestnuts.
Break frozen peas apart and spread over salad.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over top.
Sprinkle with sugar, then cheese, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Cover and chill in refrigerator for as long as 24 hours. Just before serving, sprinkle with eggs, bacon and arrange tomatoes.

title: scotch crispies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Stir until mixture is smooth. Add Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Press mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch container.
Chill.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 48 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: egg mustard dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour over romaine and mushroom salad.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
well
and store tightly covered. Use 2 teaspoons or amount desired to 1 cup boiling water.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cook mixture of pineapple, sugar, flour and lemon juice until thick.
Cool well.
Slice bananas in bottom of pie shells; add nuts.
Pour pineapple mixture over bananas and nuts.
Spread Cool Whip on each pie.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Add vanilla.
Beat eggs well. Add all dry ingredients.
Fold in cornflakes, oatmeal and coconut. Dough will be quite stiff.
I use my hands.
Just drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
They will come out round.
Bake at 350° 9 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Skin chicken and boil until done with onion soup mix and celery (about 30 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add rice.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with cranberry sauce.
Low calorie and very filling.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and water.
Knead with hands until dough is well mixed.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pinch off small pieces and roll in hands for finger lengths.
Bake in slow oven (275° or 300°) for about 45 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack jars with first four ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes and pour over okra; seal.
Makes 5 to 7 pints.
Process in boiling waterbath for 5 minutes.
Wait 1 month to eat.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Mix well but do not stir more than 2 minutes.
Pour into hot, well-greased iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: microwave popcorn balls
directions: Combine butter and marshmallows in large microwave bowl. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed.
Add Jell-O; stir until well blended.
Pour mixture over popcorn and peanuts.
Stir to coat well.
Shape into balls or other shapes with greased hands.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add blueberry pie filling, nuts and drained, crushed pineapple.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
When jello is hard, spread with topping.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar, French mustard and thin with the pineapple juice.

title: salsa
directions: Cook 1 1/2 hours or longer for thickness you like.
Put into jars and process in hot water bath for 35 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey pot pie
directions: In casserole dish, layer the ingredients as given above, chicken (cooked), then add 1 can Veg-All (drained) over chicken; add onion and 1/2 stick butter (melted), 1 can chicken soup mixed with 2/3 can water.
Pour over onion.
Mix 1 cup Bisquick with 1 cup milk and pour evenly on top.
Bake in long casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Serve with tossed salad or slaw for a complete meal.

title: sweet potato pie(servings:  8)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in dash of salt until soft (approximately 45 minutes).
Peel.
Add sugar and butter, then all other ingredients as listed above.
Beat with mixer about 2 minutes. Pour into uncooked pie shell and cook for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine mashed sweet potatoes with the rest of the ingredients.
Beat well by hand or with mixer.
Fold into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean and top is firm and golden.
Serves 6.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Steam or microwave onion and bell pepper until tender, 3 minutes if microwave.
Mix onion, bell pepper, ground beef, corn, rosemary, oregano, marjoram, salt and black pepper in large skillet or saucepan.
Combine tomato sauce and enchilada sauce. Pour half the sauce mixture over beef mixture and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator.
Can keep in refrigerator for a month.
Can freeze.

title: easy nut bread
directions: Beat egg and sugar until light.
Add milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for one hour.
Cool on wire rack.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel and grind pears, peppers and onions together.
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices.
Cook together until tender over very low heat for 12 to 15 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: brock's fruit salad
directions: Prepare all fruits as directed.
Mix orange juice and cherry syrup with a wire whip and pour over fruit.
Mix well. Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Serve when chilled.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse beans; put in large bowl.
Slice onions into rings and add to bowl.

title: peach crisp
directions: Peel, core and dice peaches.
Place in a greased pie plate. Stir in Grape-Nuts and cinnamon.
Top with dabs of butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chocolate chips and paraffin.
Shape into logs.
Dip into a glaze made from melted chocolate and paraffin together in double boiler.
Yields 40 logs.

title: purple cow
directions: Place grape juice concentrate in a 13 ounce soda glass.
Pour in about 1/2 cup of club soda and stir until well blended.
Add ice cream; pour in enough club soda to fill glass and serve. Makes 1 drink.

title: hamlins white sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well with a mixer or blender.
Chill 24 hours.
Great dip for chips or on baked potatoes.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Pour over oyster crackers. Mix well.
Let set for at least 1 hour.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans together and mix well.
Roll into a ball and coat with pecans.
Chill.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Wrap all ingredients, except the cheese, in foil, double thickness, keeping seams of foil closed tightly.
Place foil on a grill over medium heat.
Cook for 35 minutes; remove from grill. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Enough for two.
May double, triple, etc.

title: nutritious monster cookies (breakfast food)
directions: Stir together flour, oats, wheat germ, sesame seeds, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Set aside. In a large bowl, whisk together oil, sugar, molasses and eggs. Stir into flour mixture just until evenly moistened. Fold in nuts and raisins. Using 1/2-cup measure, drop 5 onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Spread each to 4-inch diameter, 1/2-inch thick. Bake 20 minutes at 375°. Makes 10 cookies.

title: paul bunyan burgers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Divide mixture into 3 equal balls.
Place a ball on a piece of waxed paper and flatten to make a 9-inch patty.
On half of patty, place rest of ingredients desired, leaving 1-inch margin.
When finished, use waxed paper to fold patty.
Pull waxed paper away from patty and seal edges.
Brush top and bottoms with oil to keep from sticking to grill.

title: spiced mocha mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium size bowl.
Stir in an airtight container at room temperature up to 2 months.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Cut jalapeno peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Stuff with cream cheese.
Wrap one half slice bacon around each cheese filled pepper.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place on a hot grill until the bacon is crisp.
Wonderful!

title: crab ball hors d'oeuvre
directions: Thaw and drain crabmeat.
Blend softened cream cheese, chives, garlic powder and salt.
Fold in crab meat.
Shape into a ball or log.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: meat-rice casserole
directions: Brown chopped onion in small amount of oil.
Add ground meat and brown; break it up as it cooks.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, green pepper, tomatoes and rice. Cook in a greased covered baking dish at 350° or until rice is done.
Be sure the rice is covered with liquid so it will not dry out and be sure the lid fits well.
(Aluminum foil works well.)

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix other ingredients and pour over flour.
Stir until just mixed.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Freezes well.
Yields 2 loaves.
(Can also be used for a cake.)

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add liquids; stir well. Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: savory vegetable crepes
directions: To use food processor:
Place slicing blade in processor. Slice mushrooms using food pusher to push food through chute, then stand celery stalks, green pepper half and wedge of onion in food chute.
Push through with pusher.
Remove slicing disc.
Replace with shredding disc with sliced vegetables still in food container.
Push through, shredding.
Remove all vegetables to skillet to cook.
Cook vegetables and sugar in butter in covered skillet over low heat until veggies are tender.
Stir in lemon juice.
Salt and pepper.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard.
Mix together.
Put in layers in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish or pan (bread, sausage and cheese).
Pour mixture over layers.
Let sit in refrigerator all night.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot cream cheese pinwheels
directions: Pastry:
In a large bowl, beat butter, cream cheese and salt with electric mixer until smooth.
With mixer on low, gradually add flour until just blended.
Flatten into an 8 x 6-inch rectangle.
Wrap and chill for at least 12 hours.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add the yeast.
Add the eggs, Crisco and mashed potatoes. Add the flour.
Knead slightly to make smooth ball. Place in greased bowl.
Refrigerate overnight, then roll out.
Let rise 3 to 4 hours. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: On large plate, spread thin layer of bean dip.
Mix taco seasoning and sour cream together and spread on top of bean dip. Layer the next 4 ingredients.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: yummy holiday dessert
directions: First Step:
In pan, cook jello, water and fruit. Stir until thickened.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cut 1/2 of berries.
Mix with sugar and water and cornstarch. Cook over medium heat in heavy saucepan until glossy.
Stir often. Add gelatin, extract, lemon juice and food coloring.
Bring just to a boil; stir well.
Remove from heat and partially cool.
Have other half berries drained.
Arrange in pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries and refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Melt oleo over low heat.
Mix with crumbs and sugar.
Press firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese in a bowl to soften; add confectioners sugar and beat.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions; fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spread evenly over crust and refrigerate 1 hour.
Top with cherry pie filling and chill for 12 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions except omit salt.
Drain well.
In a small saucepan, cook the onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in the bread or cracker crumbs.
In large mixing bowl, stir together the soup and yogurt.
Stir in the beans.
Transfer mixture to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread or cracker mixture over top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until the mixture is heated through and crumbs are golden brown.

title: easy ricotta cake
directions: Prepare yellow box cake mix according to directions.
Pour into greased and floured glass 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat Ricotta cheese, sugar and eggs until blended.
Pour over center of cake mix.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients. Add pecans and raisins.
Bake 45 minutes or until done at 325°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In a bowl, mix first four ingredients.
In a greased 9 x 13 pan, layer tortillas and mixture, starting and ending with tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream margarine; add cheese and remaining ingredients.
Form into balls.
These can be made with an olive in the center.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until firm.

title: hot chow chow relish
directions: Mix with wooden spoon only.
Clean onions and grind in food grinder.
Clean and cap peppers and grind.
Combine in large dishpan onions, peppers, sugar and cover 1/2 inch over mixture with vinegar and add salt and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly to keep from sticking about 1/2 hour.
When mixture starts to candy or stick to edge of pan remove from heat and can in pint glass jars.

title: pistou(pesto)
directions: Blend in blender until a smooth paste.

title: spicy franks
directions: Brown wieners in butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallow cream.
Bake in a 9
x 13-inch
pan
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Take from oven
and while
still hot, spread a large jar of marshmallow cream on top. Let cool.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Put margarine, marshmallows, food coloring and vanilla in top of a double boiler and heat until mixture melts together.
Remove from fire and add cereal.
Working with a small amount of mixture at a time, form into miniature wreaths.
Decorate with 3 red cinnamon candies on each wreath.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients.
Add peanut butter.
After melted add cornflakes.
Form into cookies and drop onto waxed paper.

title: dark banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in wheat germ. Cream together butter or margarine, sugar and molasses.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas and milk.
Beat after each addition.
Pour mixture into a greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly.

title: baked rice
directions: Put all ingredients in a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour

title: cheese and macaroni
directions: Boil and drain macaroni; mix with other ingredients except soup.
Place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread soup over top.
Cover dish with foil and bake on 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix 1/2 cup crumbs, meats, potatoes and egg in large bowl. Add milk, then seasonings. Shape into balls and roll lightly in remaining crumbs. Melt 3 tablespoons butter in hot skillet. Add meat balls and brown evenly on all sides. Cover and cook about 15 minutes until thoroughly cooked.

title: chili rellenos pie
directions: Line ungreased 8-inch pie pan or square pan with dough pressed together in bottom and up sides.
Sprinkle cornmeal on crust. Combine cheeses; reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix chilies with remainder and sprinkle over crust.

title: garden spanish rice
directions: In a heavy skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil and 1 tablespoon margarine and stir-fry beets for 1 minute.
Do the same for each of the vegetables separately.
Fry onion, garlic and green pepper until golden; add soy sauce and tomato sauce.
Let simmer for 1 minute.
Mix in each of the vegetables one at a time, mixing well to coat with sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Place tuna in a sieve; rinse slightly under running water. Drain.
Mix apples, celery and eggs with tuna chunks.
Squeeze lemon juice over mixture.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Serve on a crisp lettuce leaf.
Yields 6 servings.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix together.
Let set in refrigerator 24 hours.
Then spread dip on pizza pan or glass dish with shallow sides.
Top with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Dip nacho chips or tortilla chips in dip.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add flour.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add other ingredients.
Put in long baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot spicy shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Pour into small souffle dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve warm with corn chips.

title: gingerbread (mama's)
directions: Blend Crisco
and
sugar.
Add
syrup.
Add
eggs, then flour mixture.
Add
soda
to
boiling water and add slowly to first mixture and beat thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until cake is springy and comes away from pan, about 30 minutes.

title: hearty twice-baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and pierce potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 60 minutes or microwave, uncovered, on high for 12 to 14 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, cook the sausage over medium heat until no longer pink; drain.

title: salisbury steak and onion gravy
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg.
Stir in 1/3 cup of soup, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Add beef; mix gently.
Shape into 6 oval patties.
Brown in a skillet over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Remove and set aside; discard drippings.
In the skillet, combine flour and water until smooth; add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and remaining soup.
Bring to a boil. Return patties to skillet.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.
Serve patties and gravy over noodles.

title: asparagus with parmesan cheese
directions: In an 11 x 17-inch baking dish, cover asparagus with water and soak for 10 minutes.
Drain and pat dry.
In a dish, toss asparagus with butter, cheese, salt and pepper.
Arrange in pan in one layer. Bake in 400° oven for 15 or 20 minutes until tender-crisp. Sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: pizza balls
directions: Mix everything but cheese together.
Place meat mixture around cubes completely covered.
Make into balls, and dip balls into flour.
Brown and cover with pizza sauce.
When done sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Spread margarine on the bottom and sides
of square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inches).
Put butterscotch chips,
cup corn syrup, 2 tablespoons margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla
in
a
large saucepan.
Heat over low heat, stirring all the time, until mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat and add 5 cups Cheerios and 1 1/2 cups marshmallows.
Mix until evenly coated.
Turn mixture into pan.
Press evenly with back of spoon.
Melt 1 tablespoon shortening in a
small saucepan over low heat.
Add chocolate chips, stirring until chips
are
melted
and
mixture
is smooth. Spread chocolate chips over
mixture
in square pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
Remove
from
refrigerator
10 minutes before cutting.
Cut into bars (6 rows x 4 rows):
24 bar cookies.

title: microwave lemon sauce
directions: Combine 3/4 cup of water and sugar in glass bowl.
Cook on High for 2 minutes or until sugar is dissolved; stir once.
Stir in cornstarch, blended with remaining 1/4 cup of water and lemon juice.
Cook on High for 4 minutes, until thickened.
Stir once. Stir in butter.
Cool slightly before serving.
Great on gingerbread or pound cake.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in 1 stick butter with the onion and bell pepper. Put in casserole dish; cover with consomme.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Melt chocolate and cool.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pans.
Measure and mix ingredients, in order listed, in large mixer bowl.
Mix 1 to 2 minutes on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally. Pour into pan.
Bake:
oblong pan 40-45 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium size bowl.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in another bowl.
Spread bean dip on big serving platter; top with seasoned avocado mixture.
Sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese.
Serve chilled or room temperature.
Fills 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Saute onion in shortening until yellow.
Add crumbs, salt and pepper, brown lightly.
Drain salmon liquid in a cup and add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Combine salmon, crumbs and liquid.
Add remaining ingredients and blend, being careful not to crush salmon. Place in 8-inch greased casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Pour mixture of these ingredients into greased skillet (probably iron skillet) and cook at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: bubbat
directions: Scald milk and cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast (dissolved) and sugar.
Add beaten egg, salt and flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise.

title: quiche
directions: Bake pie crust to about 7/8 done.
Mix all ingredients in bowl and pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop at least 5 qts. of popcorn. In sauce pan (at least 2 qt. size), melt oleo and add brown sugar, karo, and salt.
Bring to a boil. Stir until it boils. Boil 5 minutes more without stirring. Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla. Pour over corn and stir. Put in oven for 1 hour at 250°. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Bring last 3 ingredients to rapid boil.
Then mix and pour over first mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and let harden.

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Mix yams, sugar, milk, salt, vanilla and coconut together. Pour into a baking dish and bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer (Crust):
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar, melted oleo, flour and 1/2 cup nuts.
Mix together; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sauce for barbecue ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients in small saucepan.
Stir and bring to boil Check for "pepper" hotness.
Add Tabasco or mustard to suit. Serve with barbecued short ribs or spareribs.

title: silver palate mocha brownies
directions: Melt together brown sugar and butter.
Dissolve coffee in water. Mix both together and cool to room temperature.
Then add 2 eggs and vanilla. Beat together in a mixer.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into greased 11 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned. Cool completely.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops, drain, season and place in casserole dish. Combine other 4 ingredients, pour over pork chops.
Bake covered at 375° for 1 hour or until pork is done.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in hot water.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix all together, including the soda and add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. May use butterscotch chips also.

title: oven fried okra
directions: Wash and drain okra.
Remove tips and stems.
Preheat oven to 450°.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine cornmeal and pepper. Dredge okra in cornmeal mixture.
Okra must be moistened from washing for cornmeal mixture to coat well.

title: warm apple pudding
directions: Slice apples thin and spread in a well-greased 8-inch pan. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and milk; beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat again for 2 minutes.
Spread over apple mixture.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 375° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with pudding sauce or cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lazy man's peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add peaches, spreading evenly.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Spread mixture over peaches.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: old fashioned dishpan cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and form into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes in 325° oven.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Put on stove and bring to boil, then cook for 12 minutes.
Take off stove; stir in margarine and chips. Then add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into large greased pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: leftover chicken for two
directions: Mix together.
Add more water, if necessary.
Heat.
Pour over cooked rice and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first
ingredients
together
well
and
add remaining ingredients.
Mix
together well.
Place in a baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle
cup grated cheese on top.
Sprinkle 3/4 to 1 cup of herb stuffing on the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Leftover diced turkey may also be used.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted boiling water.
Brown onion, pepper and ground beef in Wesson oil.
Drain noodles.
Mix with corn, soup and tomatoes.
Add the two mixtures.
Pour into a baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken for 30 minutes; strip meat into strips.
In mixing bowl, mix the milk, tomatoes and green chillies and cans of soup with mixer.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer half of the Doritos, meat, mixture and cheese.
Repeat, but put remaining layer of cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well; serve with fresh fruit of your choice.

title: easy cobbler
