directions: I have used 1 pkg. frozen blackberries, 3 c. fresh, blackberries, peaches or apples.
Fresh fruit is always peeled, sliced and simmered in a pan with a pad of butter for just a few minutes (just to make them a little soft).
No water necessary, fruit will produce its own.

title: idiot's delight
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and arrange peaches evenly over the bottom.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the peaches evenly, dot with oleo or butter and bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes. When cool, serve with ice cream or nondairy whipped topping.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and let stand for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Dough will be soft.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on slightly floured board. Cut into rolls.
Place on well buttered pan.
Let rise until double in bulk in warm place (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes until brown.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: chicken divan(grandson's favorite)
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and arrange in bottom of dish.
Arrange chicken pieces over top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; put over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and buttered crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven about 25 minutes.

title: sally's vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix all ingredients in a glass or plastic container.
Let it stand in a warm place for 48 hours.
It may smell sour and liquid may form on top, so stir before each use.
Use now or store it in the refrigerator, but always leave at least 1 cup starter.
Feed once or twice a week with 1 cup flour, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 cup milk.
Do not use for 24 hours after feeding it.
If you feel generous, give 1 1/2 cups plus recipe to a friend.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Cool.
Then mix in eggs and vanilla. Mix flour, cocoa, salt and pecans together and add to liquid mixture.
Grease and flour pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven when top of pie begins to crack.

title: hamburger-potato-corn casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; slice thin and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Place on top of potatoes.
Spread creamed corn on top of hamburger mixture.
Add small amount of milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover; bake 15 minutes more.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp.
Add 2/3 of shrimp to mixture and form into a ball.
Roll ball in remainder of chopped shrimp and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers.

title: apricot buttons
directions: Rinse apricots with cold water.
Cover with water and cook until very tender.
Mash through a coarse sieve and add 1/3 cup sugar.
Cook slowly until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Make into patties.
Dip in a slightly beaten egg, roll in cornflake crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven until golden brown.

title: pork chop hash brown supper
directions: Place hash browns in bottom of flat, glass baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream with enough milk to have a consistency of thick gravy.
Pour half of sauce over potatoes and half over the onions.
Arrange pork chops on top and spread remaining sauce on top.
Sprinkle with rest of onions.
Cover and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: parmesan catfish
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large zip-top plastic bag.
Add fillets; seal bag and shake to coat fillets with cheese mixture.
Place on broiler pan coated with cooking spray; discard remaining cheese mixture.
Broil 3 inches from heat (with electric oven door partially opened) for 10 minutes, or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Makes 8 servings.

title: doggie donuts
directions: Have you child mix the dry ingredients in a large bowl with their hands.
Add the egg, chicken broth and warm water.
Stir with a wooden spoon until a lump of dough forms.
You may have to take over at this point; the dough gets pretty stiff. Add more flour, if necessary, so the dough is not too sticky for little hands.
Flour the work area and roll dough to cut bones from or roll donuts.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: summer salad
directions: Place enough dressing to cover the bottom of your salad bowl. Add celery, cucumbers, onions, peppers and radishes.
Toss well and refrigerate.
Just before serving, slice the tomatoes and cut the slices in half.
Arrange the slices around the outer edge of your plates and make a bound of salad in the center of each. Sprinkle chopped parsley on top.

title: sugar pecans
directions: In large bowl, sift sugar, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
In second large bowl, mix egg white and water.
Blend until frothy, but not stiff.
Add pecans and mix until coated.
Add sugar mixture to cover pecans well.
Spread on cookie sheet (ungreased) and bake at 300° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: virginia spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat the milk in a saucepan. Add the salt and stir in the cornmeal gradually.
When smooth, beat in the butter and eggs.
Pour the mixture into a well greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: raspberry fudge balls
directions: Beat cream cheese in small bowl until smooth.
Add melted chocolate.
Mix well.
Stir in crumbs and preserves.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in almonds, cocoa or sugar.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: 3 minute fudge
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and cook about 3 minutes after coming to a boil.
Remove from heat; add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Spread out in a buttered oblong dish or drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: quick enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and stir together.
Add sauce and soup.
Simmer.
Break up tortillas or Doritos and layer alternately with the meat sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: passover nut and raspberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg yolks and sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Add juice and rind of lemon.
Add jelly, walnuts, cake meal and potato starch.
Add salt to egg whites. Beat until stiff.
Fold into yolk mixture and pour into angel food pan.
Sprinkle with more nuts.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and cream cheese. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add flour, salt and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan and place in cold oven. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and mix other ingredients, then add pecans.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Turn oven down to 300° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Jell-O, oil and flour in mixing bowl.
Add berries (save juice for glaze) and 1 egg.
Blend and then mix well, slow speed, and add one egg at a time, beating well after each egg. Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour over crackers.
Mix well.
Let sit for at least 1 hour.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off wings and discard.
Cut wings in half.
Mix ingredients and pour over wings.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Arrange wings in baking dish.
Pour some of the marinade over wings.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, turning once.
Can be served or frozen and reheated later.

title: heaven's delight
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick margarine on low heat.
Beat remaining stick of margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add 4 eggs, flour and soda alternately with buttermilk and mix until smooth. Add melted candy bars; mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with pineapple; add pecans, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Serve anytime.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add sugar slowly.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at
a time.
Beat well.
Add flavorings and flour.
Beat until light and smooth.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done at 275°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly. Reserve 1 tablespoon.
Press remaining mixture into pie shell.
Mix pudding with milk until thick.
Spoon over peanut butter mixture. Spoon Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with reserved peanut butter mixture on top of Cool Whip.

title: "sybles" squash casserole
directions: Cut and cook squash; drain.
Put squash (lightly salted) in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour tomatoes onto squash.
Top with cheese.
Crumble crackers on top.
Put in oven, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes to brown top of casserole.

title: irish cream
directions: Whip eggs; add all ingredients.
Stir well and pour into containers.
Store in refrigerator right away.
For a richer taste, double recipe and add small bottle inexpensive Irish cream.

title: cody's penne pasta
directions: Cook pasta and set aside.
Brown and crumble sausage and set aside.
In large sauce pan, saute garlic in oil for 3 minutes. Add alfredo sauce, mushrooms, pasta, and sausage.
Simmer uncovered on medium heat for 10 minutes.
Serves 4 big eaters.

title: guacamole tacos
directions: *It is better to squeeze fresh garlic through a press.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Tie celery and pickling spice loosely in a piece of cheesecloth.
Place in boiling water and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Arrange sliced onions and shrimp in alternate layers in a bowl.
Add bay leaves.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour over onions and shrimp.
Cover and chill for about 24 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: the best blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Mix together. (Blue cheese comes in 4 ounce brick, you need to crumble it with a fork.) Serve over crisp salad.
Not low-calorie, but delicious.

title: philmont special
directions: Mix well and let set for 20 minutes, covered, with damp cloth. Roll into 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into bite size pieces and drop into hot fat until brown.
Great for a snack.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Pour off fat and add all seasonings and tomato sauce.
Add chopped tomatoes.
Cook noodles according to the package.
Soften cream cheese and mix with the sour cream.
Then mix everything together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: carp de boardo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put carp on pine board over turkey pan (to catch drippings).
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Take out and let cool.
When cool, throw the carp away and eat the board.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Slice butter 1-inch thin slices and top pie.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese clouds
directions: Separate dough into 12 biscuits. Press or roll each to 1/4-inch thickness. Mix sugar and cinnamon in shallow dish. Dip cream cheese cubes in melted butter, then roll in the cinnamon-sugar.

title: allison's very yummy dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in a food processor and pour into a glass bowl or ramekin.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until lightly brown on top and bubbly on the sides.
Serve with slices of French baguette for dipping.

title: citrus chicken with peppers
directions: Place chicken breast halves in large skillet.
Arrange bell pepper strips around chicken.
In small bowl, combine orange juice, lime juice, honey, paprika, salt and pepper; blend well.
Pour over chicken and peppers.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes until chicken is no longer pink.
Using slotted spoon, transfer chicken and peppers to serving plate; keep warm.

title: salmon appetizer
directions: Mix ingredients together, except sour cream and dill weed. Place in a shallow 8-inch serving dish.
Place in refrigerator. One hour before serving, frost with 1/2 pint sour cream; sprinkle with dill weed.
Serve with Old London Melba rounds.
Serves 8.

title: rice o'bryan
directions: Saute pepper and shallots in margarine.
If using crawfish and ham, add now and saute with seasoning.
Add olives and stir in rice.
Simmer until heated thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Sprinkle crackers over bottom of casserole dish.
Using 3 layers, alternate ingredients:
oysters, celery, onion, butter. Sprinkle with lemon juice and top with crackers.
End layer should be crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place sliced cucumbers, onions and peppers in a large container.
Sprinkle with salt and ice and cover.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place over low heat.
Keep turning pickles until mixture reaches boiling point. Do not boil.
Bottle while hot in hot jars.
Seal.
Let stand 48 hours before eating.
Makes 8 pints.

title: hot sausage soup for crock-pot
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces.
Put all ingredients in a large crock-pot for 12 to 14 hours on low or 6 to 7 hours on high.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix pudding dry into the cottage cheese.
Then add pineapple and fold in Cool Whip.

title: zesty soup
directions: Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Let simmer until flavors blend.
This is delicious and will serve 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in 2-quart baking dish.

title: chocolate oreos
directions: Dip Oreos into chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: joan's banana bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add bananas, but do	not
beat until smooth.
Add flour by thirds, beating only until well mixed.
If using nuts, mix with last addition of
flour before
adding
to
batter.
Pour	into greased and floured pans. Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes until top springs back when touched lightly and sides pull away from pan.

title: egg  custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted butter, flour, milk and vanilla. Stir well and pour into a well buttered and floured dish or pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes its own crust.

title: squash delight
directions: Cook squash in water (covered tightly) for 12 minutes, or until tender; drain well.
Add other ingredients to squash, except crumbs, cheese and 2 teaspoons margarine.
Stir well.
Put crumbs on top; add cheese and dot with butter.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Boil whole, unpeeled zucchini for 8 minutes.
Slice lengthwise and scoop out middle.
Mash or blend with browned sausage and onion.
Add cheese, spices, cracker crumbs and egg.
Refill the zucchini with mixture and top with more Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: heavenly hash popcorn
directions: Spread popcorn on a buttered jelly roll pan or baking sheet. Sprinkle with marshmallows and peanuts.
Arrange chocolate bars over top.
Heat at 300° for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly and toss. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from broth. Quarter canned biscuits and add to broth.
Debone chicken and add to broth.
Simmer until done.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add butter, beaten eggs and Parmesan cheese to hot spaghetti.
Put in pie pan and form like a crust with spaghetti.
Add Mozzarella cheese in center.
Pour sauce and hamburg mixture over cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add Mozzarella cheese on top of sauce and bake 5 minutes more.
Cut and serve like a pie.

title: rodney's spaghetti
directions: Put ground beef in frying pan and brown; drain grease out of pan.
Put hamburger back in it, then add spaghetti sauce.
Let it simmer, then add the garlic powder.
Recipe is for 1 or 1 1/2 pounds of ground beef.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well and keep in tight container.
To use:
Add 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas and margarine together first, then add other ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix horseradish and dry mustard well.
Melt preserves and apple jelly in saucepan over low heat.
Mix with horseradish and mustard.
Add ground pepper.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps well for a long time.
Good with ham, pork or poultry.
Good "dipping" sauce with chicken fingers.
Can be spread over the top of a block of cream cheese and served as an appetizer with assorted crackers.

title: coated popcorn
directions: Boil until thread in cold water.
This makes 3 quarts of popcorn.

title: old fashion dressing
directions: Mix well and set aside.
The longer it sets, the better. It will get thicker as it sets. Use on fruit salad, slaw or carrot and raisin salad.

title: quick and easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk thoroughly and until slightly thick.

Add Cool Whip and mix together. Place layer of wafers in bottom of 3-quart dish. Top with 2 bananas, sliced. Add half of pudding mixture. Repeat with a second layer of wafers, 2 bananas and rest of pudding mixture. Refrigerate couple of hours or overnight before serving.

title: gelatin shakers
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Cut into squares or press cookie cutters into gelatin.
Lift shapes from pan and serve.

title: watermelon spice
directions: An old chicken is best for soup.
Cut up, add half pound lean ham and four quarts cold water; bring slowly to boil.
Boil gently until chicken drops from bone.
Skim out chicken.
Add half cup rice.
Cook slowly until rice is tender. Cut white meat of chicken into small pieces and add to broth.
Stir in 2 cups rich milk thickened with a little flour.
Season with salt, pepper and butter.

title: shrimp or crab fondue
directions: In double boiler, melt cheese and heat soup.
Add shrimp or crabmeat or both.
Add mushrooms and sherry; simmer until all ingredients are blended.
Serve with toast points for dipping. Keep warm over chafing dish.

title: chicken roll ups
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Add chicken, soy sauce and stir- fry until chicken is cooked.
Remove chicken from pan and set aside. Place onion, garlic, celery and ginger in the frying pan and cook until tender.
Return chicken to the pan with onion, celery mixture.
Add duck sauce, water chestnuts and red pepper.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often.

title: creole pork and spaghetti
directions: Brown onions and meat in skillet.
Mix with spaghetti, tomatoes, cheese and salt.
Place in greased baking dish. sprinkle crumbs on top.
Dot with butter and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, peanuts and water together. Slow boil 15 minutes or more until peanuts stop popping. Turn off heat when strings from candy to spoon. Add soda and pour immediately into greased tins (3 small tins).

title: grandma's beef roast
directions: In a heavy pan, brown a roast well on all sides, using a little suet in the pan for your drippings.

title: 1 hour rolls
directions: Let scalded milk cool to lukewarm.
Add all ingredients together in bowl.
Let rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Roll out on floured board.

title: honey carrots
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine and honey in saucepan and stir until melted. Place carrots in ovenproof casserole with cover. Pour honey mixture over carrots and toss. Bake at 400° for 1 hour for baby carrots; bake at 400° for 30 minutes for regular carrots. Stir occasionally to coat carrots with honey mixture.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: jean's irish brown bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and cut in butter.
Make a well and
stir in buttermilk.
Pour dough out on well floured board (it
will
be
a
bit
sticky), but sprinkle with flour (whole wheat).
Gently form into a ball.
Knead over a couple times and place
ball
on a round pan and then cut a cross on top of dough. (This is so the inside will bake through.)

title: super easy barbecued pork chops
directions: Pour ketchup into pan.
Slowly stir in Coca-Cola.
Place pork chops into Pyrex baking dish.
Pour sauce over.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
(Thicker chops may require more time.)

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and chill.

title: date nut log, bars or balls
directions: Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
After mixture is cold, roll into logs or balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: pickled bell pepper
directions: Wash peppers in sudsy water until squeaky clean.
Cut peppers into bite size pieces and pack in hot clean jars.
Put 1 garlic bulb and 1 jalapeno pepper in each jar.
Fix only 1 jar at a time. Boil the ingredients (water, salt and vinegar) to a rolling boil and pour over pepper in the jar.
Seal and turn upside down in a dark place for 24 hours.
Remember, fix only one jar at a time, and keep everything hot at all times.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Stir until well blended.
Allow to cool. Add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and chocolate.
Pour into greased, long and shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 48 squares.
When cool, cut in 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: vinegar drop dumplings
directions: Put
vinegar,
water, sugar and 2 tablespoons butter on stove and
bring
this
to a boil.
Take flour, 1/3 cup butter and milk, mix
together and by teaspoon drop in liquid.
Cook slow.
When done, add lemon extract.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place layers of the vegetables in the order given in crok-pot. Season each layer with salt and pepper. Put the lightly browned ground beef on top of the celery. Mix the tomato soup with the water and pour into crok-pot. Cover and set to low for 6-8 hrs. (High 2-4 hours stirring occasionally).

title: bacon dressing
directions: Mix together salt and flour.
Add vinegar and cream.
Blend well.
Cook sauce in 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings, until thickened.
Add bacon and eggs.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange layer of potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with some onion.
Sprinkle some combined flour, salt and pepper on top.
Dot with some butter.
Repeat layers until all are used, ending with butter.
Pour milk over all. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake in moderately hot oven at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until tender.

title: patio cooler(makes 3 quarts)
directions: Mix water and sugar together and boil, then all to mixture of all ingredients and chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: fudge squares
directions: Mix well.
Cook in modern oven at 300° to 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients; add salt to taste.
Serve in a dip dish with tostados or chips.
Sprinkle with lemon juice to keep from darkening.

title: apricot nectar pound cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add eggs 1 at a time and beat well. Cook in a greased tube pan in a 350° oven.

title: beef stick
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into 3 rolls.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate for 36 hours.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: Mix together and put pudding on top of Philadelphia cream cheese mix.
When completely set, spread Cool Whip over all and top with nuts.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions.
Make pudding.
Poke holes in cake with fork while still warm and pour kahlua over it.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Cut cake into 1-inch squares.
Layer in a glass bowl as follows: 1/2 cake squares, 1/2 pudding and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with half of crushed candy bars.
Repeat.
Great for large parties.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; pour in rhubarb.
Beat eggs and mix all together.
Make into paste; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put strips of dough on top and bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes or longer.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and slice potatoes.
Add the diced onion; set aside.
Cut bacon into 1/2-inch squares and cook until crisp. When done, pour bacon and grease over top of potatoes and onion. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix about 2 tablespoons sugar with vinegar.
Add this sweet-sour mixture to potatoes and bacon and mix thoroughly.
After mixing, add more salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
Do not refrigerate!

title: limas celeste
directions: Cook limas in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Drain chestnuts and mushrooms.
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients except onion rings together and pour into greased casserole.
Put onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip walnut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Pour into ungreased tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes for tube pan or 45 minutes for loaf pans.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak or roast into cubes.
Brown steak, chopped onion, margarine, garlic juice and salt.
Add mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and flour.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Combine evaporated milk and lemon juice.
Add this to meat mixture.
Heat through, but don't boil.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: saltine-chocolate bars
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar. Place saltines in a 5 x 7 rectangle on a greased cookie sheet.
Place in a 375° oven for 15 minutes until brown and bubbly.
Remove from oven and pour on chocolate chips. Let stand 3-5 minutes, then spread chocolate with knife.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water in Dutch oven until tender, about 30 minutes.
Drain well.
Mash potatoes until smooth.
Add cream cheese, 4 tablespoons butter, garlic salt, pepper and remaining 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix until smooth.
Gradually add heavy cream, mixing until smooth.

title: melt in your mouth chicken
directions: Saute chicken breasts in butter for 10 minutes on each side. Combine seasonings in bowl and pour over chicken.
Cover it and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and set aside 3 tablespoons flour and 1 1/2 cups sour cream.
Sift flour into broth mixture and cook until thick and bubbly.
Slowly add sour cream and continue to stir until gravy-like.
Pour gravy on chicken or put chicken in gravy.
Serve with rice, if desired.

title: turtles
directions: Stir milk and syrup together and boil approximately 15 minutes until a firm ball stage.
Grease cookie sheet.
Place 3 pecan halves for one candy on sheet.
Drop caramel mixture by teaspoon on top of pecans. Place one square of chocolate on each candy. Spread chocolate when melted.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers 5 minutes in salty water.
Slightly brown ground beef with onion.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and divide in peppers.
Place in skillet.
Add 1 cup of water (more if needed) and simmer 40 minutes.

title: lemon tarte
directions: Mix flour, margarine, sugar and pecans together.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Layer in order the mashed avocados; season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir in 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Layer sour cream, picante sauce and cheeses.
Top with black olives.
Serve with chips or by itself.

title: caramels
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart saucepan.
Add sugar and salt. Blend in syrup and gradually add milk, stirring constantly, to 240° on candy thermometer.
Add vanilla when done cooking.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
When cooled, turn out on cutting board and cut into bite size pieces.
Wrap in wax paper squares.

title: collard green soup
directions: Simmer sausage in water for 45 minutes.
Add shredded collards and drained beans to meat and cook 30 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper and potatoes.
Season and cook until potatoes are tender. Add more liquid if desired, such as ham or chicken broth.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid and sugar in a gallon container with enough hot water to dissolve ingredients.
Add can of pineapple juice. Fill remainder of container with cool water.
Mix in ginger ale (1/2 and 1/2) and serve.
Kool-Aid mixture may be frozen in rings or cubes.
Serves 20-30.

title: ms. cross' shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and serve with crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl and mix well with hands. Form into loaf or loaves.
Place in baking dish and cover with catchup and brown sugar mixture (and use bbq sauce if desired). Cook at 350° about 1 hour depending on the size of your loaf.
You can make smaller loaves and freeze after cooking.

title: chocolate chip cookies with snap! crackle! pop!
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt. Set aside. Blend together butter and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients. Mix until combined. Stir in Rice Krispies and chocolate chips. Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: paella valenciana
directions: In salad oil in large Dutch oven or paella pan, saute chicken pieces until golden brown; remove.
In same oil, saute onion and garlic.
Add chicken broth, pepper, salt, tarragon, paprika and saffron; bring to boil.
Add rice; cook covered over medium heat until 1/2 liquid absorbed.
Now, add tomatoes, shrimp, chicken and chorizos; simmer covered about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, steam clams, etc.
Add peas and artichoke hearts to mixture.
Place clams (lobster tails) on top; pour melted butter over all.

title: brown rice
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add rice; brown, stirring often, to a light brown.
Add boiling water; stir.
Turn heat down to simmering.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add bouillon cubs, soy sauce and, if dried down, add 2 cups more water and simmer until done, but not soft or mushy.
Serve with stir-fry vegetables and beef or chicken.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Cream the oleo, Crisco and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add 2 3/4 cups sifted flour and eggs alternately.
Add vanilla and butter flavoring.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with butterscotch morsels, pecans and salt.
Add to mixture.
Place in well-greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli into small flowerets.
Chop onion.
Fry bacon until very crisp.
Break into small bits.
Combine these ingredients; let stand for awhile.
Combine raisins, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix and let stand for awhile.
Combine both mixtures and let stand several hours; stir occasionally.

title: layered delight
directions: Bake in rectangular glass dish at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: banana cake(heritage recipe)
directions: Cream oleo and sugar, add eggs and bananas.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: cinnamon-applesauce swirl salad
directions: Dissolve candies and gelatin in water; stir in applesauce. Chill until partially set.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Mix cheese, cream and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir gently into jellied applesauce mixture.
Chill until firm.
Serve squares on greens.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: In a large mixing bowl, put about 2 cups of flour.
Make a well in center of flour.
Pour in 1 cup hot broth, mixing with a fork as you pour.
Stir egg into flour-broth mixture.
Work with fingers until a hole stays in dough when you punch your finger into the dough.
Add more flour, if needed.
Roll very thin and cut into strips.
Break strips into 3-inch pieces and drop into boiling chicken broth.
Cook until tender.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream butter, sugar and sweet potatoes; add milk and eggs. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to milk and egg batter.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Place in greased muffin tins. Sprinkle a dot of cinnamon on each muffin.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: In a 9 x 10-inch pan, put butter, then layer other ingredients evenly in the same order as listed.
(Make sure milk is spread evenly over the top.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: lemon rice pudding
directions: Spread over pudding and return to hot oven to brown, 4 to 6 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour. Add eggs and cream. Blend well. Add butter and mix well.
Line crust with nuts.
Pour the other mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond roca
directions: Mix and cook on medium-high heat for approximately 5 minutes or until nice and brown.
Add 1/2 cup nuts and cook until dark in color.
Pour out on foil-lined cookie sheet.
When cool, frost with melted chocolate chips.
Sprinkle with nuts and frost other side.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs, mixing well. Stir in pudding powder.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to butter and sugar mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for about 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: best ever chocolate fudge
directions: Put chocolates and marshmallows in a large bowl and set aside.

title: dave's sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, soy sauce, garlic and pineapple juice.
Put the pork chops in a large Ziploc bag and pour the juice over them.
Let them sit in the refrigerator overnight.

title: hard candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in pan.
Cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to hard crack stage (300°) or until when dropped in water, you can break into pieces.
Remove from heat; add food coloring and oil.
Stir well and pour out on powdered sugar on cookie sheet.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together at low speed until blended.
Beat at high speed 5 minutes.
Divide batter into 2 large greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, increasing temperature to 350° for an additional 15 minutes.
(Can also be baked in 4 small loaf pans.)

title: stuffed green peppers with shrimp
directions: *Can mix or match or increase to 1 1/2 or 2 pounds if you really want it loaded with seafood.

title: orange julius(fat-free)
directions: Mix yogurt, orange soda and pineapple in blender.
Add sweetener, if desired.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together; put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° until firm.

title: infallible souffle
directions: Remove crusts from bread; cut in half.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
Layer bread, ham, Cheddar cheese and Swiss cheese.
Repeat layers.
Combine and pour over the casserole the following:
dry mustard, eggs, onion salt and milk.
Put few pats of butter on top before baking.
Can be made the day before and refrigerated.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or longer, if necessary, depending on your oven heat.
Serves 10.

title: easy bean salad
directions: Combine ingredients in medium size bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: velveeta mostaccioli
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add beef and brown.
Add spices.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, water and bay leaf.
Pour sauce over noodles.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese and Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken couscous
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Pat the chicken dry and season it with salt and pepper.
Add to skillet with the turmeric and saffron.
Cook until browned, about 3 minutes per side.
Stir in the chopped onions and cook for 2 minutes more.
Add 1 can of the chicken broth and the tomatoes (breaking them up with a spoon), turnips, pearl onions, cinnamon stick, parsley and cilantro sprigs.
Cook until liquid is reduced by three quarters, 20 minutes.
Add the zucchini, peas and jalapeno chili.
Bring to a simmer and cook for 2 minutes.

title: deacon strawberry punch
directions: Note:
Must be made one day in advance.
tags: unsweetened cherry flavored soft drink mix

title: hot cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan, placing cloves and cinnamon sticks in a teaball or cheesecloth bag.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Serve piping hot.

title: frozen patio punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale and beat until fluffy in blender.
Freeze.
Pour room temperature ginger ale over frozen punch.
Serves about 20.

title: veggie bars
directions: On ungreased cookie sheet spread crescent rolls.
Pinch together to cover cookie sheet.
Bake as directed on package. Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, dressing and garlic. Spread on crescent crust to suit your thickness.
Cut up variety of vegetables (radishes, green peppers, cauliflower, broccoli, cherry tomatoes, shredded carrots) and arrange on top.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and serve.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Shake chicken pieces in flour with poultry seasoning.
Put oil in shallow baking pan or on cookie sheet.
Place chicken and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Mix pineapple, sugar, catsup and soy sauce. Pour over chicken and bake another hour with foil on top.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon, mashed potatoes, eggs and 1 cup cracker crumbs. Shape into patties or balls.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot oil.

title: strawberry layer dessert
directions: Slice berries and set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Chill until partially set.
Beat mixture until light and fluffy. Fold in nondairy whipped topping.
Chill until spreading consistency.
Transfer 1 1/2 cups of mixture to small bowl.
Fold in berries.
Split cake crosswise, making 3 layers.
Fill between layers with berry mixture.
Frost top and sides with remaining whipped topping mixture.
Chill.
Yields 16 servings, 112 calories per serving.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles and set aside to cool.
In a skillet, fry ground beef (crumbly consistency) until done; add taco seasoning and drain well.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, start layering (noodles, ground beef, cheese, etc.).
If you are using refried beans, cook in a saucepan to warm up for easier spreading consistency.

You can serve beans as a side dish or implement them into your pan, but add beans next to noodles for easier spreading. After layering, cover with plastic wrap and put in microwave (rotate at 5 minute intervals) until warm throughout and cheese is melted.
At this time, you can put droplets of sour cream on top and garnish with chopped green onions.

title: italian noodle casserole
directions: Crumble, brown and drain meat.
Add onion, green pepper, tomato sauce and spices.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Place cooked noodles in baking dish.
Pour meat sauce over noodles.
Sprinkle cheeses over top.
Arrange mushrooms over all.
Bake at 350° for 34 minutes.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: mom's ripe banana cake(one bowl method)
directions: Sift flour. Add sugar, shortening (Crisco), 1/2 cup bananas and eggs. Beat 2 minutes at slow to medium speed. Add remaining bananas and vanilla; beat 1 minute more. Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: seasoned parmesan popcorn(preparation time:  5 minutes)
directions: Combine margarine with Mexican seasoning; mix well.
Drizzle over popcorn; mix well.
Add cheese; toss to coat evenly.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: company baked french toast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place bread slices in dish. Lightly beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in milk; pour mixture over bread.
Turn bread to coat well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Combine flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Turn bread over again.
Scatter blueberries over bread.
Sprinkle evenly with crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Top with strawberries to serve.

title: nutzencracker snax
directions: Pour crackers and peanuts into a greased roasting pan.
Boil the butter, sugar and corn syrup for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda and vanilla. Stir until foamy.
Pour over cracker mixture and stir.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Turn out onto waxed paper.
Break up when cool and dry. Store in tins or glass jars.

title: real biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut oleo into dry mixture.
Dissolve yeast in warm buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Work through as little as possible.
Knead one time.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes in preheated oven.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix prepared rice, tuna, soup and milk; place in casserole. Top with bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ham and pork together well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix again.
Shape into a loaf and place in a low baking dish.
(A 9 x 13-inch cake pan works well.)
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, uncovered.
If loaf seems too brown too soon, it may be covered lightly with foil toward the end of baking.

title: roast with red wine
directions: Place roast in Dutch oven or roaster.
Place onion slices over top of roast.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over roast. Cover tightly and cook at 250 degrees for 5-6 hours.
Serves 12-16.

title: spoon rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, yeast and sugar.
Add egg, water and oil.
Beat well.
Spray muffin tins with Pam and fill half full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Mix will keep in refrigerator up to 3 weeks in airtight container.

title: super spinach alfredo lasagna
directions: Soak noodles in hot water for 15 minutes.
Brown sausage and drain.
Drain noodles.
Combine sausage, spinach, alfredo sauce, salt and pepper and set aside.

title: velling
directions: Cook white rice.
Take cooked rice and add 1 cup milk.
Let rice absorb some of the milk and reheat slowly, but do not boil. Beat egg and add it to 1/4 cup milk; stir egg and milk mixture into rice.
Add dash of salt and ground cardamon.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve hot with pancake or maple syrup.
Some may like additional milk.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place chicken meaty side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour half the spaghetti sauce and half of the Parmesan cheese over the chicken.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Pour remaining sauce and cheese over chicken.
Bake for an additional 20 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate raspberry truffle
directions: In heavy gauge saucepan, combine morsels, heavy cream and butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth. Stir in raspberry jam.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Freeze 20 minutes.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Freeze 15 minutes.
Roll into balls.
Freeze until firm. Coat each ball with cocoa or confectioners sugar (optional). Makes 4 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Parboil sweet potatoes until tender; mash. Combine next 5 ingredients and mix well. Pour into a well-greased baking dish. Combine last 4 ingredients and sprinkle on top of potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Place peeled and sliced potatoes in the bottom of a greased casserole. Dot with margarine, combine all other ingredients and pour over potatoes. Bake at 375 degrees for 2 hours, stirring after 1
1/2 hours.

title: curried artichoke heart rice salad
directions: Cook rice with 1 or 2 chicken flavored bouillon cubes and no butter.
Cool.
Add onions, green pepper and olives.
Drain the artichoke hearts and chop into bite-size bits.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan or 2 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Let cream cheese set to room temperature.
Prepare cake mix as directed in 13 x 9-inch cake pan and bake.
When cake is done, punch holes in it and spread pineapple and juice over it.
Prepare pudding as directed; mix cream cheese in pudding.
Spread over cake.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef.
Add beans and salt; simmer 10 minutes and drain. Toss with rest of ingredients.

title: mounds cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is baking, cook 1 cup sugar, 1 cup milk and marshmallows until melted.
Stir in coconut and spread on cake. Bring 2 cups sugar, cocoa, 1/2 cup milk and butter to a boil. Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Beat until thick and creamy. Pour over cake.

title: oven baked french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Peel potatoes and cut into strips about 1/2-inch wide. Dry strips on paper towels. Spray all sides with Pam.
Spread strips on a cookie sheet in a single layer.
Place in oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Turn occasionally.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add pineapple juice and chill.
Before serving, add chilled ginger ale to Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.

title: burritos
directions: Remove tortillas from package.
Spray pan with oil.
Place meat, taco seasoning and water in pan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in salsa and black olives. Heat beans in another pan.
Warm tortillas as directed on package or can serve at room temperature.
Distribute equally all ingredients on tortillas (beans first, then meat mixture, then cheese, lettuce and tomato).
Fold or roll up and serve.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook 4 cups of water with the rice until the water cooks away. Then add 4 cups of
milk and simmer until tender and milk is nearly all absorbed.
Remove from fire; add 1 cup raisins, 2 cups sugar, vanilla, oleo and a little cinnamon.
Stir well and pour into a large bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and chill.

title: weight watchers salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with crushed pineapple and juice.
Mix 2 minutes. Fold Cool Whip into the mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Top with corned beef, then cheese.
Combine mayonnaise and Thousand Island dressing.
Spread over cheese.
Top with tomatoes.
Melt oleo and add bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Microwave for 15 to 17 minutes on High or until heated through.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes about 6 servings.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a large bowl, make a stiff batter of ingredients. Grease another bowl and put dough in; turn over to oil all sides. Cover lightly with foil and let rise all day. That night, punch dough down and knead a little. Divide into 2 parts and knead each part. Put into greased loaf pans and brush top with oil. Lay a piece of waxed paper over pans or cover with damp dish towel. Let rise overnight. Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes. Butter top of each loaf after it is cooked and wrap with plastic wrap while it is warm.

title: cheddar shrimp dip
directions: Combine cheeses, onion, parsley and Worcestershire sauce in medium bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until thoroughly blended. Fold in whipped cream and shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: indonesian peanut sate
directions: In blender, place onion, lime juice, soy sauce, garlic and broth.
Blend until smooth.
Place meat and marinade in a plastic bag and refrigerate for about 4 hours.
Remove the meat and save the marinade.

title: grandma's fruit salad
directions: Combine drained fruit cocktail, chopped dates, mini marshmallows, diced bananas, diced apples and chopped walnuts. Mix in 3/4 of the whipped cream.
Pour the salad in a serving bowl.
Spread remaining whipped cream over the top.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: finger salad
directions: Press crescent rolls out on flat cookie sheet.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Beat the cream cheese, sour cream, Ranch dressing mix and sugar together.
Spread on cool roll bread.
Mix vegetables together and press lightly on cheese mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: sammy's jim dandy sundae
directions: Take the 4 ice cream sandwiches and squish them.
Add pudding, chocolate chips and diced banana.
Put cherry on top and enjoy.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt and cool chocolate and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: sponge dessert
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and salt and add next 3 ingredients gradually.
Add egg yolks with milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven in pan with a little water in the bottom.
Gets like cake with lemon pudding on top.

title: captain pete's fish chowder
directions: Brown bacon in pot.
Add all other ingredients, except fish. Bring to a boil.
Then simmer until vegetables are done.
If cooked fish are used, add it when vegetables are done.
If raw fish or shrimp are used, add it when you turn down the chowder to simmer. Simmer 35 to 45 minutes.
Add water if needed.

title: graham squares
directions: In double boiler, combine eggs, sugar and butter.
Cook for 25 minutes.
Must be cold when mixed with remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Put in buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix vegetables and relish.
In a pretty glass bowl, layer cornbread, vegetables and dressing; second layer as first.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Crumble bacon on top and serve. Good for a salad to serve with fish or anytime.
Unusual but good.

title: peanut crunch custard pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and put into 8-inch pie pan for crust.
Use 1 custard flavored dessert mix, cooked and cooled for 15 minutes. Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg. Cool and serve.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix milk and cherries first.
Add drained pineapple and nuts. Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Chill until firm.
Enjoy!

title: divinity
directions: Mix together sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart casserole.
Loosely cover with a lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High (100%) for 5 to 6 minutes or until boiling.
Uncover. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until hard boil stage is reached.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly pour hot syrup over egg whites while beating at a high speed of mixer.
Add vanilla and continue to beat for 4 to 5 minutes or until candy holds its shape.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Quickly drop teaspoons of candy onto waxed paper or pour into a buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: breakfast sticky buns
directions: Generously grease a Bundt pan and sprinkle bottom with pecans. Place 24 frozen rolls or dough balls over pecans.
Sprinkle pudding over rolls and set aside.
Melt margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over dough.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until top is golden.
Remove from oven and immediately invert onto serving platter and let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 adults.

title: tomato beef salad canton
directions: Cook pasta as package directs; rinse with cold water and drain. Drain tomatoes, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Combine reserved juice, vinegar, oil and soy sauce.
Pour over noodles, tomatoes, steak, onions and cilantro; toss.
Serve chilled or at room temperature. Garnish with toasted sesame seed, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream
margarine and shortening.
Add sugar;
beat until mixture is
smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Combine flour and soda;
add
to
creamed
mixture,
alternately with buttermilk. Stir in
vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour
batter
into well greased 9 x 13-inch sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: christmas rice
directions: Mix all together and pour into a large greased casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Taste when liquid is nearly gone, and if rice isn't soft, put the lid on to finish cooking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: paul hornick stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Mix together.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: hungarian cabbage rolls
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Core cabbage and boil until leaves are tender.
Roll mixture in cabbage leaf (tuck in sides).
Layer cabbage rolls, sauerkraut and onion.
Cover with tomato juice.
Add enough water to cover rolls.
Cook for 3 1/2 hours on low heat.

title: northern fry chicken mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Wash and dry chicken.
Skin chicken. Shake it in plain flour.
Dip it in 2 beaten eggs.
Then roll it in the mix.
Let it stand until soaked through.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a medium bowl.
Mix eggs, milk, and oil together.
Pour into dry ingredients and blend well. Pour out onto a hot griddle, flip over until golden brown.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Mix soup and water.
Layer in a greased casserole: rice on bottom, then chops.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy toasted sandwiches
directions: Place the slices of bread on a cookie sheet.
Top each slice with 1 tablespoon of salsa.
Crumble 2 slices of bacon onto each slice.
Put the chopped onion on top of the bacon, dividing it among the 8 slices.
Finally, put the shredded cheese on top of all the sandwiches.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Bring to a boil and stir.
Add peanut butter and mix thoroughly.
Add corn flakes and mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased wax paper.

title: swiss pie
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Reserve drippings.
Crumble and set aside.
Cook onion in drippings until tender, but not brown; drain.
Blend in sour cream, slightly beaten eggs, salt and pepper.
Add cubed cheese and crumbled bacon.
Pour mixture into shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks and buttermilk.
Mix until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until stiff. Remove from heat.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into baked 10-inch pie shell.
Top with your favorite meringue (using the leftover egg whites).
Bake according to your meringue recipe. Cool, then refrigerate.

title: brownies with cream cheese topping
directions: Mix brownie mix according to instructions.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
In food processor, whip cream cheese, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour on top of brownie dough. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash okra.
Remove ends of pods.
Cut okra into 1/4-inch slices.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix meal and flour.
Roll okra in mixture and fry in hot fat until golden brown.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef and about 1/4 chopped onion, covered, until meat changes color and onion is tender.
Add spices, salt and beans.
Cook tortillas in oil just enough to make them soft.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Use double boiler.
Chop all ingredients into double boiler except shrimp. Allow to simmer 1 hour. Add shrimp 10 minutes before dip is ready.
Serve with Ruffles or tortilla chips.

title: nicholas' hunky soup
directions: You have to make the broth.
You have to make the noodles. Put the vegetables in it.
I think you have to wait for a while to cool.
I think you cook it for 10 hours on hot.
I think it's ready in 1 minute.
You eat it with a spoon, or, if it's no more noodles, you can hold the bowl and drink it.
Just eat it with your hand.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening and whip with a fork until like whipped cream.
Shortening wil be completely melted.
Add milk; then add sifted flour with salt.
Roll out on floured board.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Melt butter in oblong pan.
Place ingredients in order on top of each other.
Last, press walnuts down on other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan over metal rack.
Cut into bars.

title: whipped topping(diabetic recipe)
directions: In a small bowl combine 1/4 c. cold water and skim milk powder. Chill.
In a saucepan cook 1 Tbsp. cold water and gelatin.
Heat and stir constantly until gelatin is thoroughly dissolved.
Add to milk mixture.
Beat with an electric mixer until stiff.
Add sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Continue to beat.

title: bran muffins
directions: Grease 10 to 12 muffin cups; set aside.
Combine bran and buttermilk; let stand 3 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in egg and oil or melted shortening.
Set aside.
Stir together the flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add bran mixture all at once, stirring until moistened (batter will be thick); add raisins.
Bake in 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients and bake in greased and floured baking pan from 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice.
Finely chop onion and saute in 1/2 stick butter.

title: simply salad(2 servings)
directions: Tear lettuce into bowl (may use other types in combination with iceberg).
Add tomato, scallions and avocado (may stop at this point and refrigerate).
Just before serving, add olive oil, garlic salt, squeezed lemon and Parmesan cheese.
Toss and serve right away.
(The garlic salt wilts the lettuce fast!)

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1/4 cup hot water, add 1/2 cup pineapple juice and then add the rest of the ingredients to the mixture. Put in mold and chill.

title: frozen pops
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients in boiling water, then add cold water.
Put into cups or freezer pops with sticks.
You can mix or match Kool-Aid with jello.

title: potato casserole(microwave)
directions: Spray 2-quart baking dish with Pam.
Layer potatoes, onions and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with margarine and cover with cheese.
Pour water on top.
Cover dish with Saran Wrap and punch a small hole in top.
Cook in microwave on High for 20 minutes or until tender.
Can be baked in oven at 350° until tender if desired.

title: veggie saute
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan; add vegetables.
Dot with more butter.
Sprinkle with soy or teriyaki sauce and wine.
Cover; cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Stir once more.
Top with cheese; cover and cook until cheese is melted.
Makes a nice light entree or serve with rice or couscous.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add beans and refrigerate. Combine salad mixture with meat.
Just before serving, add 1/2 to 1 bottle Catalina dressing.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Crush Ritz crackers.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and chopped pecans. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar (1/2 cup) and vanilla. Beat.
Fold in egg whites to cracker mixture.
Pour into heavily buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.
Garnish with fruit, if desired.
Keep chilled until serving time.

title: creamed corn
directions: Put corn with pulp, butter or margarine and water in pot. Cover; bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Mix together milk, sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to keep the mixture in a liquid form.
Pour mixture into corn.
Stir and let simmer.
Total cooking time approximately 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased casserole dish.
Makes one large or two medium casseroles.

title: mock whipped cream
directions: Put milk in fridge and a stainless steel bowl and beaters from electric mixer in freezer for 1 hour.
Put milk into chilled bowl; add 1 teaspoon each of pure vanilla and of brandy.
Beat at high speed just until peaks are formed.
Use immediately.

title: crunchy trail mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Store in an airtight container. Yields 8 cups.

title: cream of broccoli
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken broth, onion, broccoli and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Place mixture in blender; cover and blend 30 to 60 seconds until smooth.

title: confetti cheese dip
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients until thick in double boiler, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly and chill. Delicious as a dip for potato chips or crackers and excellent between thin slices of buttered (white or rye) bread for sandwiches.
Will keep a week or more, covered in refrigerator.

title: grandma's potato donuts
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, eggs, oil, milk and vanilla.
Sift nutmeg, cinnamon, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix all ingredients well.
Drop into hot grease.
Drain.
Shake in sugar. This is a great way to use leftover mashed potatoes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan which has been oiled and heated in oven.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425° until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour until it looks like corn meal.
Combine beaten egg, water and vinegar.
Add this to the flour mixture; mix well.
Freeze.
Yield: 4 to 5 pie crusts.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Make cake; let cool 15 minutes.
With large meat fork, poke holes at 1/2-inch intervals in the cake.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water.
Pour slowly over entire cake until all is used.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: scandinavian almond cake
directions: Spray (deerback or saddle mold)
pan or loaf pan with Pam or cooking spray. Beat sugar, egg, almond extract and milk.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add butter or margarine and mix well. Sprinkle sliced almonds on the bottom of pan before pouring batter in.
Bake at 350° for 40 - 50 minutes.
Edges must be golden brown.
Cool in pan before removing.
Cake will break if removed too soon. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop all vegetables in large pieces.
Mix together well and pour 3/4 cup canning salt over mixture.
Let stand 2 1/2 to 3 hours, then drain real good.

title: carnation meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Pour into loaf pan. Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: five-spice wings
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove wings and place on broiler rack. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, turning and basting with marinade every 15 minutes.

title: strawberry angel food trifle
directions: Purchase or make an angel food cake.
Scrape off browned crust.
Break apart into small pieces.
Whip 1/2 pint carton of whipping cream and mix with can of Eagle Brand milk, 1/2 cup lemon juice and frozen strawberries (thawed, using juice).
Layer 1/2 cake, 1/2 of mixture, 1/2 of cake and 1/2 of mixture in a pretty bowl.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: hunter's venison stroganoff
directions: Heat oil and simmer peppers and garlic until soft.
Add oregano, tomato paste and wine.
Simmer until tasty and add venison and sliced olives.
Layer over cooked lasagna noodles.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: cranberry carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and lightly flour (on bottom only) a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Combine cranberries, toasted pecans and the 1/4 c. flour in bowl of a food processor, fitted with steel blade.
Process until cranberries and pecans are finely chopped.
Set aside. In another bowl, combine the carrots and oranges.
Mix well.
In large bowl, combine oil, sour cream and brown sugar.
Beat until blended. Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Add carrots and oranges. Beat well.
Combine the 2 cups self-rising flour, cinnamon, and baking soda.
Stir to mix. Add cranberry mixture to the flour mixture.
Add to the oil mixture slowly, beating until well blended. Add vanilla and mix. Pour into pan and bake for about 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake.
Cool completely on a rack before frosting.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients until thick and bubbly.
Let cool completely.
Then add mandarin oranges.
Stir in Cool Whip and chill until firm.

title: cheese-broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in West Bend slow cooking pot (or small skillet over) over medium heat or range top unit.
Add onion and saute until glossy.
Transfer cooking pot to heating base using hot pads or pour skillet-sauteed onion into slow cooking pot.

title: martha's sweet potato pie
directions: Bake 1 hour at 300°. Use one deep-dish pie crust or 2 regular ones.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix tomato sauce and salad dressing with vegetables.
Add cheese, celery, salt, pepper and garlic salt to your own taste. Mix thoroughly with spaghetti and chill overnight.

title: touchdown bars
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and butter until crumbly; stir in chocolate chips.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir milk, egg, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Pour on crust.
Bake again 25 minutes.
Remove and cool.
May add chopped nuts and coconut.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Grease 10-inch tube pan and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Dissolve soda in water; cool.
Cream Crisco and sugar until fluffy. Add egg yolks one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add soda water.
Sift flour and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk and flavorings.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to batter, folding in gently.

title: tortilla appetizer wedges
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine with sour cream in bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in chilies, onions and jalapenos.
Spread one tortilla with scant 1/4 of mixture; top with another tortilla.
Continue spreading and stacking tortillas until stack is 4 high.
Top with 5th tortilla (do not spread on mixture).
Make another stack of 5 tortillas.
Wrap stacks in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least one hour.
Before serving, cut each stack into 18 wedges.
Arrange, pinwheel fashion, on a plate around a bowl of salsa or picante. Makes 36 wedges.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in oil in large skillet, stirring frequently. Add soup mix and 2 cups of water; cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Stir green peppers into steak mixture.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup of water.
Add to mixture in skillet.
Cook until thickened.
Serve with rice or riced potatoes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheeseburger macaroni casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce to ground beef.
Simmer on low.
Make macaroni and cheese mixture according to instructions on box.
Add macaroni and cheese mixture to beef mixture; put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Shred Mozzarella cheese on top; crush potato chips on top of cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: raw vegetable pizza
directions: Prepare pizza crust mixes according to directions.
Bake and cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix; spread on cooled pizza crust.
Chop raw vegetables; spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Chill. Cut with pizza cutter.

title: chewy bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in greased wide pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool and cut in squares (like brownies).

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients 3 times.
Boil the water.
Add to the Miracle Whip or mayonnaise; stir with whisk.
Add to dry ingredients; beat well.
Pour into a 9 x 7-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 35 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: centennial vienna bread
directions: Mix 3 cups flour, 1 cup milk and 1 cup water together to make loose batter.
Set aside for 45 minutes, then add 1 cup warm milk with the salt, sugar and yeast dissolved in it.
Add the rest of the flour at intervals.
Knead after each addition.
After flour is completely added, knead dough until elastic.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise for approximately 2 1/2 hours or until dough is doubled.
Butter hands.
Divide dough into 2 pieces.
Knead each piece slightly.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Let rise in a warm place until dough is doubled again.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Loaf will sound hollow when thumped.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Combine apples, 3/4 cup sugar, butter and cinnamon in saucepan.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening with sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Spread over apples in pan.
Bake at 350° in oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven.
Turn cake upside-down over large serving plate.
Let stand a few minutes, then remove pan.
Makes 16 servings.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and warm water; let stand 1 minute.
Add to the flour.
Cut in the shortening.
Add yeast mixture and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover bowl; put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: andrea's bread
directions: Melt in microwave margarine for 1 minute.
Add milk and sugar and microwave 3.5 minutes.
In mixer mix bread flour and dry yeast.
Add wet ingredients to dry; cover and let rise in warm place, 1 to 2 hours.
Separate into three greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: yellow summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Mix all ingredients; pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: carter's peanut butter sticks
directions: Trim crusts.
Cut each slice into 4 lengthwise strips.
Mix oil and peanut butter until it is the consistency of honey.
Dip bread slices in mixture and coat with bread crumbs.
Place coated slices on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 150° for 3 hours (can be baked for up to 6 hours) or until dry and crisp.
Cool on racks.
Makes 80 sticks; 37 calories per serving, 2 grams of fat, trace of cholesterol and 36 milligrams of sodium.

title: mild cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients well and roll into ball.
After ball gets firm (refrigerate), then roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together with mixer or food processor.
Wet hands and form into 2 balls or logs.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: oh-so-good chicken
directions: In heated skillet melt half the butter and oil.
Cook chicken over high heat for 2 minutes on each side.
Transfer to warm platter.
Add chives (or green onions), lemon juice, brandy, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly. Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately. Good with pasta or rice.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugar, soda and buttermilk until boiling over medium heat.
Continue cooking until it has a brown color and makes a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Stir until it has a glossy look.
Add pecans.

title: jalapeno peppers
directions: Slice potatoes in 1/4 rounds; boil until tender and drain. Make sauce with milk, flour and cheeses; add salt and pepper to taste.
In a large baking dish, layer potatoes (half of recipe), onion, green pepper and pimentos, then make another layer of same. Pour sauce over all; bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: poor boy's stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes. Add soup and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through; do not boil.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: rice and meat balls
directions: Soak bread in milk. Mix bread with meat and onion.
Make into balls and brown.
Place these in casserole.
Mix celery soup, water and Worcestershire sauce together and pour over meat balls.
Bake in a 350° oven. Serve with rice.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well; set aside.

title: german apple cake
directions: Blend all and beat as package directs.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes (until top springs back).
Cool.
Top with whipped cream sprinkled with cinnamon.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple carrot bread
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add carrots, oil, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Spoon into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients in microwave and stir to mix.
Add Crispix and mix until coated.
Place confectioners sugar in bag. Add chocolate mixture and shake until coated.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, salad oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt. Let stand while preparing remaining salad ingredients or refrigerate overnight.
Gently toss all ingredients together.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray an 11 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican macaroni
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper. In a large saucepan, combine tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and seasonings. Add beef mixture and simmer a few minutes. Add macaroni and cook until tender; add water as needed.
Pour into a large greased casserole and top with thick slices of Cheddar cheese.
Bake about 20 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate peanut bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup melted margarine, egg and flavoring well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 13 to 16 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and return to oven.
Bake for 3 to 4 minutes, until marshmallows are puffed, not brown.

title: corn relish
directions: In large saucepan cover corn with water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain.
Then stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes.
Spoon into clean jars.
Seal hot caps and jars.
Makes 6 pints.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put the chicken breasts in a casserole dish.
Cover with cooking wine.
Sprinkle with last four ingredients.
Put in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini.
Be careful not to overcook.
Strain and pour into large bowl.
Add artichokes (cut in half), carrot pieces, celery, pepperoni or salami, olive pieces and can or jar of pimentos.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate. Serve with Hawaiian bread.

title: joe's cheese cake
directions: Blend together.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill for 4 hours.
Top with whatever you would like.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Put in baking dish. Crumble 1/3 box Ritz crackers with 1/2 cup margarine to put on top.
One half cup slivered almonds may be added.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry or blueberry cheese cake
directions: Melt butter and stir in crumbs.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: domino brownies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Prepare brownie mix according to directions on package. Cool.
Frost brownies with vanilla frosting.
Cut int 6 lengthwise strips about 1 1/2 inches wide.
Cut in 4 crosswise strips about 3 inches wide.
Remove brownies from pan.
Decorate tops of brownies with chocolate pieces to look like Dominos.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork. Add shortening, sugar and beaten egg. Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Add nuts and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Place meat in a large glass bowl.
Pour hot mixture over meat, cover and refrigerate
for 2 days.
Drain meat, strain and save liquid.
Dry meat with a paper towel and rub well with seasoned flour.
Brown meat in a Dutch oven on all sides.
Add strained marinade and bring to a boil.
Cover tightly, reduce heat and simmer 2 1/4 hours.
Add carrots, whole onions and simmer 1 hour longer or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Transfer meat and vegetables to a heated platter.
Skim fat from liquid in pan; measure liquid adding more water if necessary to make 4 cups liquid total.
Return liquid to pan; add sugar, salt, crumbled gingersnaps and simmer until thickened, stirring constantly. Slice meat.
Serve with vegetables and gravy.
Great with potato pancakes and red cabbage.

title: lois flake's lazy cake
directions: Oil a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Spread the pineapple in an even layer in the dish.
Spread the dry cake mix over the pineapple. Add the brown sugar evenly.
Next sprinkle the nuts over all. Finally cut the margarine in thin slices and scatter it on top. Do not stir.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: missouri slaw
directions: Shred head of cabbage.
Crumble Ramen noodles and add to cabbage.
Add seasoning packets from Ramen noodles.
In separate bowl, combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Mix and pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss to mix.
Eat immediately.

title: good 'n cold dessert
directions: Prepare whipped topping according to package directions. Crumble up cookies and chop up the walnuts.
Mix into the whipped topping.
Spread half of this mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dot sherbet over the top and smooth it out. Put the other half of the whipped topping mixture over the sherbet.
Put in the freezer until hardened.
It's nice and refreshing!

title: pasta and vegetable salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
In a small jar with tight-fitting lid, combine oil, lemon juice, water and salad dressing mix and shake well.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except lettuce.
Toss with dressing.
Cover.
Chill several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Serve on lettuce.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: apple-date cake
directions: Cream together shortening and granulated sugar; add egg and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and blend.
Stir in apples and dates.
Spread in greased and floured 11 x 7-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts; evenly sprinkle over top.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Good served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: dump cake
directions: Put all ingredients in 9x13 inch pan in the order given.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel the eggplant; cut in chunks.
Cover with salt water and soak for 1 hour.
