Drain and stew with a little more water until tender (about 15 to 20 minutes).
In a mixing bowl, combine the next 5 ingredients.
Should be juicy.
If not, add a little water. Put in a greased casserole and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Lay the cheese slices on top and heat until cheese is melted.
May also add sausage links, if desired.

title: dump cake
directions: Whip eggs. Mix cake filling into eggs and fold in pie filling. Pour mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° following directions for baking on cake mix box. Test doneness about 35 minutes.

title: creamed peas
directions: Butter a casserole dish and set aside.
Melt oleo in saucepan and fry onions until they soften.
Add flour and stir until smooth. Add milk and stir until sauce thickens and boils.
Remove from heat.
Season and add peas.
Stir well and pour into casserole and bake at 350° until hot, about 20 minutes.
May be topped with bread crumbs if desired.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble the sausage into a pan.
Put flour on top of meat. Brown this together until done and lightly brown.
Pour milk on top of this to make the gravy.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Use as much flour as you think is needed for thickness desired.

title: tomato basil tart
directions: Bake tart crust in pan at 425° for 10 minutes.	Remove from oven and sprinkle with mozzarella cheese and let cool. Slice tomatoes thin and drain on paper towels.
Arrange tomatoes on melted cheese in crust.
Combine basil leaves, garlic, mayo, parmesan and pepper in processor.
Spoon mixture evenly over tomatoes.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375° until bubble.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry and banana mix
directions: Thaw strawberries in large bowl.
Peel and slice bananas. Place bananas in bowl with thawed strawberries.
Cover mixture with Jell-O.
Refrigerate for approximately 2 hours; stir occasionally. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Add taco mix and water. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: baked french toast
directions: Melt butter and sugar in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Cut bread into thick slices.
Layer bread over sugar and butter in two layers.
Beat eggs, half and half and vanilla.
Pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown.
Serve each person 2 layers so they get brown sugar bottom.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Bake cake in oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan as directed on package; cool.
Cut cake crosswise in half.
Reserve 1/2 for another dessert.
Cut remaining cake into 8 pieces; split each piece horizontally.
Arrange half the pieces in a 2-quart glass serving bowl, cutting pieces to fit bowl.
Pour half the strawberries (with syrup) over cake; spread with 1 cup of the pudding.
Repeat with remaining cake pieces, strawberries and pudding.
Cover.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: glazed apple nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl beat brown sugar, margarine, cinnamon, vanilla and eggs until smooth.
Stir in quick bread mix, apples and raisins just until blended.
Pour in prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until comes out clean when checked with toothpick.

title: broccoli dressing
directions: Cook onion in
butter until tender.
Add rice, cream of mushroom soup and
half
can
water.
Cook and drain broccoli. Mix all together.
Pour
in
casserole and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let set a little while before serving.

title: theresa's tex-mex chicken
directions: The selection of chili peppers is up to you.
I, personally prefer a fairly hot jalapeno, but suit your own taste.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot, according to your manufacturer's particular directions.
Cook until chicken falls apart.

title: texas beans
directions: Fry onion and bacon.
In large pan, add all beans, along with catsup, syrup and barbecue sauce.
Diced green pepper may be added. Stir and cook for 1 hour.
Really good for a large crowd!

title: connie's fresh apple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, salt, spices and egg until well blended.
Stir in 1/2 of flour/soda mix, then nuts, apples and raisins.
Blend in juice (or milk) and add rest of flour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake for 11 to 14 minutes or until done.
While still hot, spread with glaze.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach.
Add dry onion soup and sour cream.
Blend. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and let set awhile in refrigerator.

title: mel neil's hot cakes(for a hearty start to a cold, windy island day.)
directions: Editor's Note:
Did they use glass cake pans, too?

title: pickle halves with tuna
directions: Cut pickles in half, hollow out center of each and put the center of the pickles in a large bowl.
Add drained tuna and eggs to bowl.
Add mayo to desired consistency.
Better if it's a little dry so don't use too much mayo.
Mix well.
Lay lettuce leaf on a platter, then put pickles on top of lettuce and fill with tuna salad.
Lettuce is mainly to make it look pretty.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Dip eggplant in egg, then in breadcrumbs.
Fry eggplant in large skillet over medium heat in hot oil until lightly golden. Drain on paper towels.
Place single layer of eggplant in a buttered baking dish.
Cover with some spaghetti sauce (not too thickly) and Parmesan and Romano or Mozzarella cheese.
Continue to layer eggplant, sauce and cheeses until eggplant is used up. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma (hume) wedge's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: green chili cornbread
directions: In small bowl combine first 6 ingredients and cumin. Mix well. In medium bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff. Set aside.
Beat egg yolk in separate bowl until frothy.
Stir in warm water and oil.
Mix yolk mixture into dry ingredients.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fold cornmeal mixture into egg whites with whisk.
Add corn and chili. Pour into 8 x 2-inch baking pan and sprinkle lightly with additional cornmeal.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Serve warm.

title: cinnamon cheese toast
directions: Butter slice of bread.
Put in toaster oven.
Let butter melt. Turn over.
Place a slice of cheese on bread.
Let cheese melt. Take out of oven and sprinkle on cinnamon and eat while warm.

title: swiss apfeltor cake
directions: In large bowl, put sugar, margarine and egg.
Beat until light and fluffy.
In sifter, sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder, nutmeg, ginger, soda, salt and cloves.
Sift dry ingredients into the sugar, margarine and egg.
Beat well (will be stiff).
Gently stir in sliced apples by hand.
Apples will blend into batter. Turn into buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Spread smooth.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.
Good with ice cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Put into a casserole dish.
Cook at 375°.
When
done,	sprinkle
buttered bread crumbs or Ritz crackers on top, then let it brown.

title: mexican mocha balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir flour with cocoa, coffee and salt.
Gradually beat with creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and cherries.
Chill this for 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.
While warm, but not hot, dust with extra fine sugar.
Makes 84 balls.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Boil meat covered with water; include bouillon cube, bay leaves, parsley, pepper, onion and green pepper.
When tender, set aside meat.
Chop all vegetables into small pieces.
Add carrots, first, then stewed tomatoes, frozen vegetables and then the potatoes.
Cut meat into small pieces and add back to soup. Add cut up cabbage last.
Add more water for thinner soup.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Freezes well!

title: hoboes
directions: Place patty and vegetables on aluminum square large enough to hold and close over vegetables. Splash with worcestershire sauce.Dot with a couple of butter pats. Seal foil over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until
vegetables are done. Serves as many as you like. This can also be used while camping or on the grill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together except bacon and put in a buttered baking dish and sprinkle crumbled bacon on top and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Mix the ground beef with chopped mushrooms, salt, chopped onion, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Spoon the mixture over the steak.
Roll the sides of the steak like a jelly roll over the stuffing.
Bind with bacon strips wrapped around the roll at regular intervals.
Fasten bacon end with toothpicks.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Slice so each serving will have bacon slice around outside edge.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked peaches
directions: Place peach halves in a shallow casserole.
Fill each half with a heaping tablespoonful of mincemeat.
Place in preheated oven at 350°.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken and broccoli
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat margarine until hot; add chicken, cook until lightly browned on all sides.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
To same skillet, add broccoli, garlic and saute for 1 minute.
In mixing bowl, combine chicken broth, oyster sauce and cornstarch.
Add to broccoli mixture and cook for 15 minutes, until tender.

title: good hot dish
directions: Put in layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: biscuit ring
directions: Place sugar, butter and water in a pan.
Heat until butter is melted.
Place 6 ounce glass or cup in middle of a 9 x 2-inch round glass dish to make ring mold.
Sprinkle nuts evenly around glass.
Cut each biscuit in half; stir into sugar mixture, coating each piece.
Arrange around cup in dish.
Cook until top springs back.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Line pan with foil, letting it extend up sides of pan.
Spread melted margarine over bottom; sprinkle with brown sugar and arrange fruit on top.
Add cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Turn out on plate, remove foil and top with whipped cream.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix in 2 1/2 quart bowl, ground beef, applesauce, precooked rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into balls.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup catsup and 1 cup water.
Pour over balls and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix 2 cups hot water with Jell-O, 1 cup cold water and 1 cup cream.
When it begins to gel, add pineapple and cream cheese.

title: nuts and noodle casserole
directions: Cut drained Tenderbits in fourths, bread with meal and brown in hot oil.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in corn oil.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Place in oiled casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar. Add 1 cup flour, salt and soda.
Mix. Add zucchini and 2 cups flour. Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pans. Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Can be frozen. Makes 2 loaves.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Spread bread slices with dressing.
On 6 slices, lay 1/2 slice cheese; on top of that 2 slices corned beef, 2 teaspoons sauerkraut, then 1/2 slice of cheese.
Top all with another slice of bread.
Spread outside of bread with butter and grill until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry applesauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan, cook the apples, cranberries, sugar, apple cider, cinnamon stick and lemon zest over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until it looks like applesauce.
Stir in butter.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 3 cups.

title: aunt jane's stolen chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
Skin and debone chicken.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth until almost tender (not soft) and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Cut Velveeta into cubes and add to hot vermicelli.
Mix vermicelli and other ingredients together.
Spray casserole dish with Pam and pour in mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serves 50 finicky eaters or 15 normal eaters or 8 people who are going on a diet Monday.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Must use mayonnaise.
Do not substitute.
Mix vegetables, onion and water chestnuts together.
Add cheese and mayonnaise. Mix well and pour into a shallow greased baking dish.
Crush crackers and mix with oleo and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: microwave barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave for 3 minutes at High.
Stir sauce once.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: single action baking powder
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in a glass jar with a lid for up to one month.

title: *pineapple slaw
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together the sour cream, salt, mustard and pineapple syrup.
Add cabbage and pineapple; mix thoroughly. Serve at once or chill for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: cherry cookie bar
directions: Mix with a pastry blender the flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add baking powder, salt, vanilla, nuts, coconut and cherries.
Spread over top of baked pastry.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir together in a skillet.
Cook 10 minutes on low heat. Cool.
Will thicken as cools.

title: refrigerated blueberry pie
directions: Mix and pour in pie shells.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sprinkle flour over cake mix and add dry Jell-O, oil, water and thawed strawberries.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Add one egg at a time until all four have been added.
Divide batter into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: run for the roses pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes in a preheated 325° oven.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, garlic, scallions, salt and pepper; mix well.
Trim beans and cook in boiling, salted water for about 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
Place warm beans in salad bowl.
Pour dressing over warm beans.
Add salami or cooked leftover ham and toss well. Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed green bell peppers
directions: Cut off tops of bell peppers, remove seeds and membrane.
If needed, trim bottom of peppers so they stand upright.
In a pan with enough boiling water to cover, blanch peppers 3 or 4 minutes. Remove peppers, drain and cool. In a large skillet add olive oil and saute onions until translucent.
Remove and reserve onions. Brown ground beef and finely crumble.
Add onions, crushed red peppers, worcestershire sauce and balsamic vinegar.
Cook over low/medium heat for 5 minutes to blend flavors.
Remove from heat and set aside. Add beef broth packet to 1 cup water and bring to a boil. Add rice, cover and remove from heat. Mix soup with 3/4 cup of water.
Add 1/3 cup soup to rice/beef mixture and mix together. Place peppers in casserole dish and stuff with meat mixture.
Add remaining soup and drizzle some on peppers. Cook peppers in 350 degree oven for 30-45 minutes.
Cut peppers in half, if desired. Makes
2-4 servings.

title: espresso cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine cookie crumbs, 1/2 teaspoon espresso coffee powder, and melted butter; mix well. Reserve 1/4 cup of this mixture for the topping.
Press remaining mixture in bottom of ungreased 8-inch square pan.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Grease muffin pans with oil or spray. Fill muffin pans and cook for about 30 minutes in a 400° oven until brown.

title: hot crab  dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except 2 tablespoons of the onions and red pepper until well blended.
Spoon onto 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish. Bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons onions and red pepper before serving. Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pilgrim pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, mix turkey, peas, corn, gravy, 2 tablespoons of the chives and the thyme.
Turn into a shallow 2 1/2 to 3-quart baking dish; set aside.

title: philly delight
directions: Spray 9 x 12 Pyrex dish with Pam spray. Take one of the crescent dinner rolls and press it down in Pyrex dish. Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg and extract in bowl. (I melt cream cheese in microwave first.) Pour over crescent roll layer in dish. Take the 2nd crescent roll and lay over cream cheese mixture. The layers may overlap. Sprinkle cinnamon sugar over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bottom layer gets slightly brown.

title: tangy meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard. Remove 4 tablespoons of the mixture and reserve for topping.
To remaining mixture, add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, onion powder, seasoned salt, pepper and egg; blend well.
Stir in green pepper and Wheat Chex.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Shape into loaf in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread top with reserved catsup mixture.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine
cup
warm water, dry yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar. Put
pint
warm
water, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, beaten eggs
and melted butter in a bowl.
Add yeast mixture and add flour; mix as for light bread.
Let rise once, punch down, put wet
cloth over dough and store in refrigerator.
Do not punch down
anymore. Pinch
off and make as desired rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: the best biscuits(1978 hereford magazine)
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Add sugar when yeast starts to bubble.
Add oil, milk and soda; mix well.
Add flour.
Put into a large, covered bowl for a few hours or overnight.
Stir slightly.
Dip out with a spoon onto floured board; roll out and cut.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 450°, or until golden brown. Dough can be kept covered in refrigerator up to 10 days.

title: mrs. stilwell's chin chews(a christmas "must"!)
directions: Frost and cut in squares.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup in deep pan.
Bring to a boil. Cook to hard ball stage or 250°.
Slowly pour over egg whites while beating with mixer.
Beat until candy clings to spoon and loses most of its shine.
Let cool.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix butter, sugar and salt until light.
Add the beaten eggs, sour cream, soda, flour and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into muffin (paper-lined) tin and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon or nutmeg, if you want.
Fill each cup 1/2 full.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: cake layers made from scratch
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add vanilla. Bake at 350° until test done. Use your favorite frosting.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Drain all fruits.
Mix together Cool Whip, Jell-O and sour cream.
Add drained fruits.
Add nuts.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan and chill.

title: warm apricot crunch sundaes
directions: Set oven control at broil. Place apricots in 8-inch ovenproof skillet or shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar and cashews on apricots; dot with butter.
Broil with tops about 6 inches from heat until sugar and butter are melted and sauce is bubbly, about 2 minutes. Serve immediately on ice cream.

title: mom's pie dough(makes 2 single or one double crust)
directions: Cut flour, salt, baking powder and shortening with pastry cutter or dough hooks.
Add milk and egg mixture until just mixed. Do not overmix, as this causes pie crust to become tough.

title: mackerel loaf
directions: Flake mackerel. Add crumbs, milk, relish, eggs, salt and butter. Mix well.
Pack into greased loaf pan.
Set in shallow pan of hot water and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Mix white sauce.

title: london broil
directions: Remove excess fat from steak, then score on both sides.
Place all the ingredients in a shallow pan.
Place steak in pan, then turn over.
Marinate at least 3 hours or overnight, turning several times.
Place steak in broiler 3 inches from heat.
Broil each side 4 minutes.
Slice thin across grain diagonally.
Serve with Bearnaise Sauce.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Combine pineapple juice and juice cubes in blender.
Blend until slushy.
Makes 2 servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook the rice according to package directions with the vegetables added. Cut sausage in bite-size pieces. Add sausage, Saffrito beans and olives.

title: garden-veggie pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Five minutes before pasta is cooked, add vegetables.
While pasta cooks, mix sour cream and dip mix in a bowl.
Drain pasta and add to sour cream.
Mix well and sprinkle with cheese to taste.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Chop cranberries in food processor and add sugar.
Let stand 1 hour. Chop peeled apples and add lemon juice.
Dissolve the Jell-O in boiling water and let cool.
Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Serves 6.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt in bowl.
Let stand 1 hour. Squeeze out water (if any). Add carrots and mango.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Boil 1 minute.
Let cool and pour over slaw mixture.
Put in containers.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp
directions: Marinate
shrimp
in
French Dressing overnight. Drain. Wrap each
shrimp
in
half
a
slice of bacon and secure with wooden toothpick.
Place
on a rack over shallow pan and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Boil spaghetti; drain.
Mix in the beaten eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Line casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for 1 cup pecans.
Form into a ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: festival corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients
(only half of crackers).
Melt butter.
Crumble remaining crackers in butter; brown slightly. Pour over casserole.
Bake	at
about
30 minutes (until lightly brown).

title: breakfast slush punch
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Add pineapple, orange and lemon juices. Freeze in containers.
Set out about 1 hour before time to use. Place in punch bowl; pour chilled ginger ale over punch.
Small slices of lime and lemon can be frozen in mixture.
Accent with mint.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 1 12 cup fluted tube an. Mix sugar and
cinnamon
in
a
gallon
plastic
bag. Working with 1 can
at
a
time, remove biscuits; separate and cut each one into 4
equal
pieces.
Coat with butter;
add to bag with sugar mixture.
Close
bag and shake to coat.
Gently press pieces into prepared pan.
Repeat with remaining cans of biscuits.

title: potatoes del monte
directions: Heat Cheez Whiz, chicken soup, cream cheese and 1/2 stick margarine together.
Blend into hash brown potatoes, onion and green pepper.
Place into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole. Crush corn flakes and mix with 1/2 stick margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: breaded deer meat
directions: Cut meat into strips approximately 1/2-inch wide by 4-inches long.
Roll in eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Roll in dry ingredients.
Fry in skillet with butter until browned.

title: oven-poached swordfish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place the swordfish in a glass baking dish.
Combine water, lemon juice, bay leaf and thyme.
Pour over the swordfish.
Bake fish uncovered for 20 minutes.
Remove fish from liquid and serve with the sauce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple bran muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs and sour milk. Add dry ingredients which have been sifted.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
For bread, bake 1 hour.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Use any hot roll recipe.
Dough should not be too stiff. After dough has risen once, roll out and spread with margarine. Fold over and chill in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Take out and repeat the process 2 more times.
Roll out again and cut in pie shaped wedges.
Starting at small point, roll up and put in greased pan not touching.
Let rise again and bake in 375° oven until light brown.
Bottom of rolls will brown quickly.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: luscious potato soup
directions: Make vegetable broth by boiling about 2 to 3 quarts water.
Add about 1/3 head cabbage, 5 to 6 celery stalks, 3 to 4 carrots, sliced lengthwise and broccoli.
Boil about 1/2 hour.
Broth may be kept in refrigerator a day or two before making soup.

title: tahitian chicken
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add chicken.
Cover and chill overnight, turning pieces occasionally.
Broil or grill outdoors until chicken is fork-tender, basting with marinade.

title: almond tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce as per package directions, using tomato paste.
Brown meat.
Cook noodles until tender.
Combine beaten eggs, cottage cheese and salt.

title: delicious cucumber pickles
directions: Cover the whole washed cucumbers in boiling water.
Let stand overnight and then drain.
Repeat this procedure for the next 3 days.
On the 5th day, drain and slice each cucumber into 1/2-inch chunks.
Combine the sugar and spices with the salt and vinegar; bring to a boil.
When boiling, pour over cucumber slices.
Let this mixture stand for 2 days.
On the 3rd day, bring the mixture to boiling and then seal in hot jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour half of mixture into greased and floured 13
x
9-inch
pan.
Bake
at
350° for 15 minutes or until
toothpick
inserted
in center of cake comes out clean.
Mix
together
1/2	cup milk, butter and caramels; melt over low heat.
Pour
melted
caramels over cake.
On top of caramels, put
nuts
and
chocolate
chips.
Pour remaining cake batter on top and
bake
at
250° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 10 minutes	or
until done.
Cool.	Cut into squares. Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: peanut raisin clusters
directions: Melt the butterscotch chips over hot water; stir in peanuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix all soups and milk in butter. Spread rice on bottom of ungreased glass casserole.
Pour half of soup mixture over rice and mix.
Salt chicken lightly.
Lay over rice.
Pour remaining soup over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt oleo into saucepan.
Add sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from the heat.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and peanuts.
Mix well and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour out onto waxed paper or cookie sheets and cool completely.
When cool, break apart and store in covered container.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift together
first
ingredients.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs
in
bowl. Add dry ingredients and margarine.
Mix only until	flour is moistened. Stir in nuts.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 5 x
3-inch loaf pan in oven (350°) for 65 minutes or until toothpick	inserted
comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add spices and salt.
Stir in syrup; add eggs, one at a time.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in oats. Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Buy the cheapest brand of dill hamburger slices.
Drain juice and fill jar with sugar.
Let set until sugar dissolves, making a crisp, sweet chip.
Add more sugar later if needed.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O in hot water.	Add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add
cold	water.	Set in refrigerator and let congeal slightly.
Add bananas, pineapple and pecans.
Set in refrigerator and congeal.

title: yoshiko's cabbage
directions: Fry bacon; add carrots and stir.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes.
Add cabbage, salt, pepper and monosodium glutamate.
Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add green pepper and onions.
Stir and fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add corned beef and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: chili sauce
directions: Blanch, cold-dip, peel and quarter tomatoes.
Chop onions and peppers.
Combine ingredients and cook mixture until it is thick. Seal immediately in clean, hot Ball jars.

title: jello salad
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch (or smaller) pan.
Sprinkle pretzels over margarine.
Dissolve jello in hot juice and frozen strawberries.
Let cool.
Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour jello mixture over pretzels, then top with remaining mixture.

title: date cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake on low in oven on long baking pan.

title: spoon packki
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs and sugar until lemon in color.
Add melted butter and lemon juice.
Add yeast that was mixed with 1/2 cup warm milk and water.
Add flour alternately and rest of milk and water until all used up (if dough is too sticky, add a bit of flour).
Dough should be heavy enough to drop off spoon, but not runny.
Let rise until double.
Drop by tablespoon into oil (375°).
Fry 2 to 3 minutes until dark brown in color so they are not raw inside.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: quick and easy chocolate cake(recipe from the depression era)
directions: Blend together the flour, sugar and cocoa. Make a "well" in the center of the mixture. Dissolve the baking soda in the boiling water. In the "well", add the scoop of Crisco (about the size of a good egg) and pour the boiling water/baking soda mixture over the top. Blend thoroughly. Gently beat the egg and fold into the chocolate mixture. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or when a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Top with your favorite frosting and voila!!! Happy eating!

title: mocha almond parfaits
directions: Spoon 1/4 cup ice cream into each of 8 (4 ounce) chilled parfait glasses.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Toast and chop almonds. Crush toffee bars.
Layer 1/2 tablespoon each of almonds, candy and chocolate syrup.
Repeat layers of ice cream, almonds, candy and chocolate.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Garnish each parfait with whipped cream and a cherry.
Yields 8 parfaits.

title: french onion soup
directions: Pour bouillon or stock in crock-pot.
Cook onions slowly in large skillet in butter.
Cover and let cook for about 15 minutes. Uncover and add sugar, salt and flour.
Stir well.
Add to stock. Cover and cook on low, 6 to 8 hours (high for 3 hours).
Before serving, top with grated cheese.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Taste for right sugar. Roll out each biscuit thin.
Place fruit on half side.
Fold over and seal with fork around edges.
Fry in oil in heavy pan until browned on both sides.

title: miniature burritos
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread 3 tablespoons mixture on a tortilla and
roll
up.
Cut
each into 3 parts; secure with a toothpick.
Arrange
on pie plate in a circle.
Cook in microwave on
High
for
2 to 3 minutes until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red cake recipe
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa; add to mixture.
Add salt, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix in vinegar and soda
but do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: curried tomato-apple chicken(low-fat)
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
In large skillet or wok, combine chicken, tomatoes, raisins and curry.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, 10 minutes or until chicken is tender. Stir in onions and apple.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Serve over couscous, bulgur or rice.

title: congealed strawberry shortcake
directions: Shred cake.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Prepare jello using package directions.
Mix with thawed strawberries in bowl.
Spread over cake.
Chill, covered, until set.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: light bread or rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm milk.
Add sugar.
Set aside to grow. In bowl, combine bread flour and salt.
Add milk mixture and melted margarine, stirring to mix.
Turn out on floured surface and knead hard for 8 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Put into a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until dough is doubled.
(An ovenproof bowl filled with hot water in oven along with the dough is a good place for the dough to rise.
Put the oven on warm before placing the dough there.
Turn oven off to let rise.)

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare muffin tins.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
In another bowl, stir milk, butter, egg and vanilla.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients and stir just to combine.
Stir in blueberries briefly.
Do not overmix. Spoon into prepared pans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in tins on rack 5 minutes before removing from tins.
Continue cooling on racks.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until it reaches soft ball stage. Add the peanuts and cook until orange/yellow. Take off heat and add the soda.
Spread out butter sheet thin.

title: ruby shake
directions: Juice enough grapefruit to make 1 cup juice; strain.
Measure all ingredients into container of electric blender.
Blend until smooth and frothy.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: french green bean salad
directions: In a casserole dish combine soup, sour cream and pimento. Stir in beans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or microwave 6 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and cracker crumbs. Place mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs. Slice margarine on top of crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: lila's feather bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies(microwave)
directions: Microwave (High) margarine in 1-quart bowl 20 seconds or until softened.
Blend in 1 cup sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Blend in vanilla.
Add flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Grease bottom only of 8-inch square dish.
Spread half of batter in dish; set aside.
Microwave (High) cream cheese in uncovered 2 cup glass measure 30 to 45 seconds or until softened.
Blend in 1 tablespoon sugar.
Spoon over batter in dish.
Spoon remaining batter evenly over top.
Cut through batter with a knife to marbleize.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.

title: rice and corn casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add cooked rice, corn and jalapeno pepper.
Pour in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: spicy black beans and tomatoes
directions: Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add olive oil.
Place over medium high heat until hot.
Add chopped onion and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Add the tomatoes and chiles. Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, for 6 to 8 minutes or until thick.
Stir in beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until hot!
Yum! Serve with rice.

title: lori's meatball cheeseburgers
directions: Dissolve bouillon in saucepan in the water over low heat.
In a large bowl, combine beef, crumbs, onion, eggs, liquid and cheese.
Mix well.
Form into patties; fry on medium heat (medium-high) in skillet, letting both sides get crisp.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken, drain and cube.
Whip cream until stiff. Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Will keep about 3 days in refrigerator.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, add roast, soup bones, tomatoes, celery, rice, bouillon cubes and onions.
Add enough water to cover roast by several inches.
Cook until roast is very tender and meat falls off the bones.
Remove all bones.
Cut or pull the meat into small pieces.
Add carrots and cook for 15 minutes, then add potatoes and cook for another 15 minutes.
Add corn, green beans, peas and all seasonings.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Bring to a boil and add cabbage.
Continue cooking on low until cabbage is tender.
You can adjust the seasonings to your taste.
Also, add water anytime if needed.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash 5 to 6 minutes and drain.
Mix onion, egg, salt, pepper, oleo and cracker crumbs.
Gently add squash.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese and bake about 10 more minutes or until cheese melts and is slightly brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Grind twice the beef, veal and pork.
Soak 5 minutes the lite cream and bread crumbs.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Fry bacon first, then dip chops in flour, with salt and pepper.
Save what's left of flour.
Fry your chops in the hot bacon drippings until brown on both sides.
Turn down heat, cover and cook until chops are tender and thoroughly cooked, about 30 minutes.
Stir your leftover flour into the fat and cook until browned.
Pour the milk over the chops and simmer until gravy is thickened.

title: plantain fritters(tostones)
directions: Peel plantain.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Soak in salted water for 15 minutes.
Remove and deep fry until brown.
Remove and flatten each slice to about 1/4 to 3/8-inch thick.
Deep fry again and drain on a paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt to taste.
Good with ketchup or garlic oil/butter.
Makes 6 to 8.

title: bacon and cheese bread
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Add to oat mixture, stirring just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: vinegar cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Flatten before baking with a flat-bottomed glass dipped in ice water.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until edges are lightly golden.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet or Dutch oven.
Pour off any grease.
Brown onion with the meat.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: italian cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and dry ingredients. Make into cookie shapes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain artichokes, saving marinade from one jar.
In marinade, saute onion.
Cut up artichokes.
Beat eggs and add crumbs and seasoning.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into a greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting into squares.
Serve hot or cold.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: cajun-style turkey stew
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in 12-inch skillet over medium heat into hot salad oil, stir flour; cook, stirring constantly, until flour is dark brown but not burned.
Add onion, celery and green pepper; cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Gradually stir in tomatoes with their liquid, sugar, salt and hot pepper sauce until blended, stirring to break up tomatoes, over high heat; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add water and peanut butter. Spoon out on wax paper.

title: spice kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar and cinnamon.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto well-greased baking sheet.
Make a depression in each with back of 1/4-teaspoon measure.
Bake in slow oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove immediately to cooling rack.
When cool, fill with 1/4 teaspoon chocolate frosting.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended. Add pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, salt and pepper; mix well. Chill. Shape into a ball and roll in pecans. Serve with crackers. Leftover cheese ball can be re-shaped and refrigerated until next event.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper until tender; add meat and brown.
Add seasonings, tomato sauce and water; let come to a boil.
Add rice; turn burner to low heat, cover with lid and simmer about 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup. Put remaining mixture in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar, lemon juice and egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 15 minutes longer. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Mix altogether and put in freezer about 20 minutes.
(Chunk all cheese to mix.)
Shape into ball and roll in pecans.
(Put pecans in blender).
Refrigerate until served.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up and skin the chicken. Discard the liver.
Boil in water about 45 minutes. Turn heat off and let cool. Remove bones from chicken and cut in bite size pieces.
To broth in pan, add the remaining ingredients.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Soak peas for 3 hours.
Drain.
In 4-quart pot, add all ingredients and cover with water.
Boil until peas are done. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagne
directions: Cut sausages in small pieces and fry with ground meat in pan, using a little olive oil.
Prepare sauce.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic in olive oil (a little bit), then add mushrooms, oregano and basil.
Gradually add tomato sauce.
After that, add Ragu sauce. Add some water and simmer, covered with lid, for 45 minutes. Always use a wooden spoon to stir sauce instead of metal.

title: old-fashioned cole slaw
directions: *Can use 1 small can partially drained shredded pineapple in place of onion and green pepper.

title: 3 fruit punch
directions: Makes 25 (6 ounce) servings.
This is a yellow punch.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add sugar, vanilla, pineapple and 7-Up. Let set in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti and cheese casserole
directions: Boil spaghetti; drain and rinse.
Melt cheese in milk over boiling water (or in a microwave).
Combine all ingredients. Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jim's margaritas
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
If you have a blender, add ice cubes to make a slush.
If you are camping, pour in a pot with
ice
cubes.
Rub
each glass or mug with some lime, then dip in salt.
Fill the glass with your drink.

title: vanilla dreams
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and cream on medium heat to 234°.
Cool slightly.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; beat.
Drop teaspoons of thickened mixture onto wax paper and allow to set.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix well and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Stir once or twice before serving.

title: layered jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello mix in boiling water.
Add pineapple with juice, pie filling and nuts.
Pour half mixture in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put in freezer to set.
Keep remaining half at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and half Cool Whip.
Spread over chilled jello; add remaining jello on top.
Chill again.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: glazed acorn squash
directions: Place squash, cut side down, in baking dish.
Add water.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until squash is firm.
Drain water, turn cut side up.
Stir together other ingredients and spoon mixture over squash.
Return to 350° oven and bake for 15 minutes (basting occasionally) or until fork-tender.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Prepare oven rack first.
Take rack out.
Fit brown paper or parchment paper on oven rack.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar in large bowl; beat until light and fluffy. Add peanut butter and 2 tablespoons milk; beat well. Prepare 1 envelope topping mix according to directions on package, using 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Fold into peanut butter mixture and spoon into baked crust. Prepare remaining envelope of topping mix according to directions using remaining 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Spread evenly over peanut butter mixture. Garnish with chopped roasted peanuts. Chill at least 5 hours before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Spread crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend until thick, oleo, eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread over crackers.
Slice bananas lengthwise over mixture.
Add pineapple.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze until ready to use.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Add onions and bell peppers to cucumbers.
Mix well with salt and cover with ice for 3 hours.
Drain water and ice (wash off salt if too salty).

title: smoked moose or beef jerky
directions: Slice meat into thin strips, about 3/8-inch thick and 1 to 2-inches wide.
Combine all other ingredients in pan big enough to hold meat.
Place meat in layers, making sure liquid is on all sides of meat.
(Can also place everything in a large Ziploc bag.) Place in refrigerator for 8 hours, turning meat once or twice. Remove meat from marinade and pat dry.
Smoke in smoker 8 to 12 hours.
Can be smoked in oven at 160° or low until done, using additional liquid smoke on each piece.
Fully dried jerky can be stored in airtight zipper bag or jar.
Will keep indefinitely in vacuum sealed bags.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and spices.
Stir into eggs.
Add cushaw, molasses and milk.
Stir well to blend.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until crust is golden brown.

title: easy fruit turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: diabetic applesauce cookies
directions: Cream oleo, Sugar Twin and egg.
Add applesauce and vanilla. Beat in sifted flour and spices.
Fold in raisins and oatmeal. Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: swedish coffee bread
directions: Simmer and cool 1 quart milk and 3 pounds margarine.
Dilute yeast cakes in 3/4 cup warm water (add 1 teaspoon sugar).
Add mixture to 3 cups sugar, 4 beaten eggs and 1 extra yolk (save white), unbleached flour and cardamon seed (crushed).
Mix well. Then put into large greased bowl.
Turn over so greased side is up.
Let rise 1 hour (maybe longer) covered in warm place.
When doubled in size, turn out onto floured surface and knead, adding more flour as needed.

title: granny hilah fox's dill dip
directions: Mix together.
Add dill juice if too thick.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Pound chicken breast with mallet slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and margarine in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side. Do not cook longer or they will be overcooked and dry.
Transfer to a warm serving tray.

title: acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half and clean out seeds.
Place on cookie sheet.
Fill each acorn squash with 1 tablespoon maple sugar, 1 teaspoon brown sugar, 1 teaspoon butter and a few sliced pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Serve.

title: aunt joane's reuben dip(microwave)
directions: Spray dish with Pam.
Combine ingredients.
Stir up.
Put in microwave for 3 minutes on High (until cheese melts).
Serve on party rye, sesame bread sticks or rye crackers.

title: glazed tropical fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 1 1/2 cups of the juice.
Put in bowl and add bananas, pecans, drained oranges and cherries.
Toss fruit gently.
In mixing bowl on high speed, beat pudding mix and pineapple juice for 2 minutes.
Pour over fruit mixture and stir gently.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: spinach and rice stew
directions: Wash fresh spinach in 3 rinses of cold water. If frozen, partially defrost.
Heat oil in saucepan and fry onion on medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add spinach.
Sprinkle rice over spinach. Add water and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and cook on low heat for 35 minutes.
Stir once or twice with spoon to avoid scorching and sticking to the bottom.
Add another cup of water if more sauce is desired.
Serve with crusty bread.

title: pineapple-cranberry salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch square pan. chill until firm (not solid).
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over firm cranberry mixture and chill.
This can be cut in squares and served on crisp lettuce leaves.

title: shrimp pasta
directions: Saute shrimp in butter, 5 minutes.
Cut into chunks.
Set aside.
Heat oil and toss in spaghetti, cheese, pepper and Tabasco.
Add cream and simmer.
Add sauteed shrimp.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: swedish biscuits
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix flour, etc. and roll into small balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes, dice everything together and add salt, pepper, and garlic salt.
Mix with enough Miracle Whip to hold it together.
Add the vinegar.
Stir.
Put into a casserole dish. Cover with sliced olives and snips of raw bacon.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 min. to 1 hr.

title: chicken and corn bread dressing
directions: Roast
Chicken:
Rub chicken in butter.
Season chicken with salt
and
pepper.	Add
1/4 cup of chopped onion, celery and bell pepper;
stuff
inside of chicken.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes per pound.	Reserve the broth.

title: lemon love notes
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and flour and press into an ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into crust.
Return to oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, sour cream, chicken soup, butter, onion and crumbs.
Spoon mixture into well-greased casserole dish.
Spread rest of Pepperidge Farm crumbs on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tofu lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Blend soft tofu in blender and combine with Jell-O mixture.
When cool, add Cool Whip and blend well.
Pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate until set.
Top with blueberry pie filling or any other fruit.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook the mixed vegetables according to directions. Add the mayonnaise, cheese and celery to the vegetables.
Place in dish and top with the crackers mixed with the margarine.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Slice chicken breasts lengthwise in narrow strips.
In a wok or deep, heavy skillet, pour oil to 1/2 inch depth.
Heat oil to 350°.
In small bowl, beat egg white until frothy.
Add 1 teaspoon cornstarch; continue beating.
Gradually add 1 tablespoon plus 2 teaspoons cornstarch, beating until egg whites form soft peaks.

title: bacon mushroom roll-ups
directions: Cook bacon and then vegetables until tender.
Stir in cream cheese until melted.
Trim crust off bread and cut in half horizontally.
Flatten bread with rolling pin.
Spread mixture on flattened pieces of bread.
Roll up jelly roll style and fasten with a toothpick.
Place seam down on baking sheet.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour or freeze in single layer.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine fruits and nuts into a 10 x 6-inch dish and refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream over this layer; gently pour remaining gelatin over sour cream.
Refrigerate until firm again.
Makes 5 to 8 servings.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix.
Add nuts and raisins.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with applesauce.
Bake in greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add seasonings and beans.
Place tortilla chips in bottom of baking dish.
Put beef and bean mixture over chips. In blender, blend tomato juice, flour, chili powder, and onion till smooth.
Pour over bean mixture in pan.
Bake at 350°F for about 1/2 hr.
Put shredded cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted.
Enjoy with extra tortilla chips.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix together salad oil and sugar; add half of dry ingredients.
Mix well and beat in carrots, pineapple and nuts; add vanilla and remaining dry ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended after each addition.
Pour into two greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and toothpick comes out clean.

title: fat man's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups; add mayonnaise or sour cream, onion and lemon juice. Mix well.
Add chicken and rice; mix altogether.
Put in large casserole dish.
Crush crackers; mix with margarine and spread on top of casserole.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: creamed cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower until tender.
Do not overcook.
Heat the soup.
Add sour cream and milk and heat again (do not boil).
Pour sauce over drained cauliflower.
Garnish with almonds and cheese. Serves 6 to 8.

title: norcutt's walnut pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: crabmeat souffle
directions: Butter a 2-quart Pyrex baking dish (7 1/2 x 12-inch).
Place 6 slices buttered bread on bottom.
Sprinkle with cleaned crabmeat. Add 6 more slices of buttered bread.
Beat eggs and add to milk. Pour over bread and crabmeat.
Add grated cheese.
Cover with tinfoil and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach ricotta tart
directions: Prepare pie crust mix, following label direction for one-crust pie. Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry; flute edge, making a high rim to hold all the filling. Prick bottom and sides with fork to keep the pastry flat while baking. Fit a piece of wax paper in bottom. Add a layer of rice or beans to weigh down. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 5 minutes. Remove paper and rice and let pastry brown about 6 to 8 minutes longer. Remove to wire rack.

title: never-fail dumplings
directions: Combine water and oleo and bring to boil.
Add flour.
Stir until mixed and leaves sides of pan.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Drop into soup by spoonfuls which is boiling.
Cook until they puff up.
(Do not overboil.)

title: cajun chow mein
directions: Mix ingredients and place in well-greased Dutch oven.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve with green salad and French bread.

title: uncle ernest brown's pepper relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions and cabbage separately.
Squeeze and discard juice from vegetables.
(Use cloth bag or cheesecloth.) As you grind peppers, add garlic gradually to grinder.
Mix all ingredients together and boil for full 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Blend well.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Blend with first mixture.
Fold in nuts. Turn into 2 loaf pans or a Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and place on foil pizza pan.
Smash down to form a crust and bake as directed.
After crust cools, spread with softened cream cheese mixed with sugar.
Layer fruit cocktail, bananas and cherry pie filling.
Makes 8 to 16 slices. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: cream cheese nut bar(very good)
directions: Mix until crumbly and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan the 1/2 cup butter and cake mix.
Beat 5 minutes the eggs, cream cheese and 1 box powdered sugar (minus 1/4 cup) and pour on top of cake mix. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup powdered sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool and slice.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons melted butter over low heat until it softens.
Do not brown.
Combine onion, bread cubes and seasonings.
Add remaining butter and enough broth to moisten. Toss to mix.
Makes 4 cups.

title: peanut butter honeybees
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream peanut butter, butter and sugar until smooth. Add crumbs; mix well. Shape teaspoonfuls of dough into 1 1/4-inch oval. Place on a waxed paper lined baking sheet. Place chocolate in a small microwave bowl.

Microwave on High for 1 minute or until melted. Transfer melted chocolate to a resealable plastic bag. Cut a small hole in corner of bag. Pipe three strips on each bee. Insert two almonds into each bee for wings. Use a toothpick to poke holes for eyes. Store in refrigerator. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: cream puffs
directions: Place water, butter and salt in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour.
Beat until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Cool 1 minute.
Add eggs, one at a time until mixture is smooth and glossy.
Use pastry bag or cookie shooter and make 1 to 1 1/2-inch mounds, 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake for 30 minutes or until puffs are golden brown with dry rigid sides.
Make slit in the side of each puff with a small knife.
Cool. Fill with pudding, whipped cream or whatever you desire.

title: crescent sandwiches(appetizer)
directions: Separate crescent rolls into triangles.
Layer 1 slice ham, cheese and turkey.
Roll the crescent rolls as normal.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix 1 cup milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Cook on low until cocoa is dissolved.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in evaporated milk and vanilla.
Pour into container of 4-quart freezer and finish filling with milk, 2 to 3-inches from top of container.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.

title: simple tuna salad(serves 4)
directions: Mix all ingredients, in order given, in a small mixing bowl.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Sift together into large mixing bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add oil, eggs, carrot, pineapple (with syrup) and vanilla.
Mix until moistened; beat 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Bake in greased and lightly floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven about 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Frost with a cream cheese frosting.

title: freezer biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to buttermilk.
Add milk to dry ingredients and mix well.
Turn out and cut out.
Freeze on baking sheet and store in freezer bags.
When ready to use, place biscuits in oven when you turn oven on (400°).
Do not preheat oven!

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel, wash and thinly slice onions.
Saute in butter and oil over low heat, uncovered.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cook for 20 or 30 minutes, stirring occasionally (until golden brown).
Sprinkle and stir in flour and allow to cook slowly for 2 or 3 minutes while stirring.
Add the onion mixture to beef and chicken broth. Simmer partially uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes.
While soup is cooking prepare bread.

title: hot chocolate mix(big batch)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in airtight container. For 1 serving, mix 1/4 cup mix with 3/4 cup boiling water.
Stir to dissolve.
Top with marshmallows or whipped cream.
Can adjust amount of mix to taste.

title: crunchy sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sauerkraut, beans, pimiento, onion and celery in a large bowl and set aside.

title: sausage and sauerkraut casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Meanwhile, brown sausage in a skillet; drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add tomatoes and sauerkraut to pork and cook for 2 minutes.
Drain macaroni; stir into skillet along with cheese.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir all together and put in graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.
Makes two 8-inch pies (heaping). So easy!

title: homestyle tuna pot pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with one crust; set aside.
Reserve second crust.
In medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour tuna mixture into pie shell; top with second crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Cut slits in top crust to vent.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna-corn chowder
directions: Add potatoes, onion and salt to the boiling water.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Add a dash of pepper and 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Bring to a boil and serve.
Serves 4.

title: brown rice
directions: Put rice in a casserole dish, uncooked.
Heat soup, water and margarine.
When heated, pour over rice and stir.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cherry salad
directions: Bring pie filling, sugar, Jello and water to a boil; let cool.
Pour in pan and let chill until set.
Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of Jello mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: creamy uncooked cherry pie
directions: Pour the cherries into crust; spread with whipped cream and sprinkle nuts over top.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: hawaiian nut sandwiches
directions: Blend milk and cheese together well.
Add pineapple and nuts. Blend well.
Good on orange or raisin bread as well as white bread.

title: green pea salad
directions: Combine peas, cheese, celery, pickles, pimento, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in medium size bowl.
Toss lightly to coat evenly. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Combine coconut and margarine; reserve 2 tablespoon mixture and press remainder firmly on bottom and up side to rim of 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Heat all but 3 squares of the chocolate with 1/4 cup milk in large micro bowl at High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted, or heat in heavy saucepan over very low heat. Beat in the cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature until pie can be cut easily.
Melt remaining chocolate about 15 seconds, and drizzle over pie.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fast pace dip
directions: Thoroughly mix together.
Serve with tortilla chips or your favorite snack cracker.

title: cheesy bread
directions: Mix together butter, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and Worcestershire.
Slice loaf of French bread in half lengthwise. Cut slices at 2-inch intervals but not quite through the bread. Spread cheese mixture over both halves of loaf.
Place on aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese begins to bubble or broil bread until cheese bubbles and browns.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix together crackers and margarine.
Press in pan.
Mix pudding and milk and pour over crust.
Let it get firm.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: bingo bars
directions: Mix eggs, oil and baby food.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Spread into 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan, greased. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool then frost.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Wash carrots; scrape if necessary and leave whole.
Cook in small amount of boiling salted water about 12 to 15 minutes or until tender when tested with fork.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine butter, sugar and cinnamon in large skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly until well blended.
Add carrots.
Cook over low heat, shaking pan often to glaze carrots on all sides.
Yields 6 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and poppy seed in a large bowl.
Beat in oil and water; add eggs one at a time, beating each well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes before turning on plate.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix together and let set in refrigerator for 3 hours before serving.
This is really good with string beans.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in bananas, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Cook in miniature bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine hash brown potatoes, onion, chicken broth and water in a large pot and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat thoroughly.

title: gelatin-yogurt dish
directions: Add 1 cup of boiling water to gelatin.
Stir until dissolved. Add yogurt.
Stir.
Chill until set.
Yields five (1/2 cup) servings.
Any flavors of gelatin and yogurt may be used.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugars, peanut butter, egg and vanilla. Beat until mixed.
Sift together dry ingredients; fold into mixture.
Chill if dough is too soft.
Roll in small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet, lightly sprayed with Pam, 2 inches apart. Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes before removing from pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish and bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
Remove from oven, spread remaining onion rings on top and serve.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a 4-quart pot over medium heat.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add carrots, potatoes and water.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in clams, including juice.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes for 5 minutes, covered.
Drain and saute in the butter until tender and golden.
Shake frequently.
Add the parsley, salt and garlic.
Serve at once.

title: crunch
directions: Spread pie filling over and chill a short time.

title: three bean chili chowder
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper until tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with chopped onion, sour cream or shredded cheese. Enjoy!

title: famous dirt cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and hold.
Mix the pudding and 4 cups milk and add first three ingredients.
Stir in 8 ounces Cool Whip. Layer in large glass bowl - cookies, pudding and top with cookies.
Add a plastic flower on top.
Makes a great conversation piece.

title: turkey noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package; drain and measure 2 cups. Place in large bowl; gently stir in diced turkey, mushroom soup, milk, bread crumbs and poultry seasoning.
Spoon into 2-quart glass casserole dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes.
Rotate after 1/2 of cooking time is over.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, water and taco seasoning.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In a 1-1/2 quart casserole dish, layer ingredients in this order:
chips (3 cups), all the ground beef mixture, sour cream, Mozzarella cheese, and remaining chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serve topped with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: "chicken romano"(origin: unknown)
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil until done.
Remove and add garlic and shallots until golden, then add vegetables.
Cook until al dente.
Add chicken, herbs, spices and cavettellis, then simmer for 5 minutes.

title: cracker toppers
directions: Put square of cheese the size of cracker on the cracker.
Put 2 or 3 apple slices on cheese, then sprinkle with a little cinnamon. Heat in microwave or oven until cheese starts to melt.
Serve warm.

title: crab rangoon salad
directions: Combine crab, cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add soy sauce, ginger, garlic, onions and celery and mix well.
Serve on lettuce.
Top with chow mein noodles.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add orange juice and stir until melted.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Let congeal. Dissolve pudding in one cup cold milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on top of congealed salad.

title: mary's corn casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute the onions in the butter.
Let cool and add the sour cream.
Stir and spread over corn mixture.
Cover with the cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and Karo.
Beat until well mixed.
Add butter, salt, vanilla and pecans and stir thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: ham and potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes covered in boiling water to cover for 10 minutes, or until tender (do not overcook).
Drain and set aside. Cook frozen mixed vegetables according to package directions; drain and set aside.

title: velvety lime squares
directions: Carefully toast 1/2 cup coconut in moderate 375° oven until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Combine remaining coconut, crumbs, butter and sugar.
Lightly press into 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan and bake in moderate 375° oven for 6 to 7 minutes. Cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix juice, egg, flour and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Then add cream cheese and chill.
Then add Cool Whip.
Dip fruit or angel food cake
cubes in to this.
Very good.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook rice; set aside
to
cool.
Toss
together olives, onions, shrimp, salt and pepper
to taste.
Chill for a couple of hours.
Stir in French dressing to your desired taste.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken parts, in a large bowl. Turn chicken pieces in this mixture until coated.
Cover; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Place chicken on rack in foil lined roasting pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until chicken is brown.
This is good served cold for picnic.
Serves 6.

title: hush puppies or corn dogs
directions: Fry in deep fat at 365°.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy carrot bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Spoon into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Blend macaroni, olive oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Toss lightly. Add olives, onions, celery, pickle and garlic powder and blend well in a tossing manner as to not crush the paste. Add mayonnaise and
mix lightly. Chill thoroughly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit and yogurt breakfast
directions: Place the yogurt spread in a medium size bowl.
Blend in the sugar with a fork.
Peel and thinly slice the banana into the yogurt.
Add the grapes and mix with a fork.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well; pour into baking dish.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break the spaghetti in half.
Cook until done.
Drain while warm.
Combine spaghetti with eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch pie plate.
Pat mixture up and around sides and bottom.

title: raisin syrup for diabetics
directions: Fold apple juice and water; add raisins and thicken with cornstarch.
Add cinnamon to taste.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix in order listed; beat well.
Bake until done.
Cool; do not remove from pan.

title: aunt jo's chicken
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Top each piece of chicken with a slice of Mozzarella cheese. Lay mushrooms over the cheese. Mix the soup with the wine and pour over the chicken. Spread stuffing mix over top and drizzle melted butter over the top. Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°. Serves 6.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup just to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter. Add cereal and mix well.
Press out in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chips together.
Spread over top.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar and egg, then add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Form in balls and refrigerate until firm.
Melt 1 pound chocolate bark and roll balls in chocolate.
Place on wax paper until cool.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Heat juice and pour over jello. Let dissolve and add the Coke.
Chip in cream cheese.
Chill until it starts to set; then add celery, pecans, pineapple and cherries.
Pour into mold and chill until firmly set.

title: chicken-fruit salad
directions: Combine chicken, grapes, pineapple chunks and apple wedges and chill until just before serving time.
Blend lightly with dressing.
Dip edges of lettuce cups in paprika, if desired, and serve salad on lettuce.
Top with almonds.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry charlotte
directions: Mix gelatine, 1/4 cup of sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks and water together; add to gelatine mixture.
Add 1 package of strawberries.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until berries are thawed and gelatine is dissolved (about 8 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add the other package of berries, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Stir until berries are thawed.
Chill until mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 7 x 11-inch pan. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients and sour milk alternately.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting with 2 teaspoons added.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and cool; combine onion, butter, pepper, salt, soup and sour cream.
Fold in potatoes and cheese.
Mix butter and seasoning mix; put potato mixture in a baking dish.
Top with seasoning mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on box, add fruit.
Refrigerate while preparing the rest.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in walnuts, coconut, carrots, pineapple and orange juice.
Fill muffin tins two-thirds full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter well.
Add sugar gradually, then beat in eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, baking soda and cocoa.
Add to cream mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at lowest speed until blended after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown ground meat and onion until well done; drain well. Slice carrots and place on top of meat.
Cook 5 minutes, covered. Slice potatoes thinly and place on top of carrots.
Pour brown gravy over potatoes; cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serve with a salad and bread.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Add food coloring and Jell-O.
Let cool.
Have strawberries in a baked pie shell.
When mixture cools, pour over strawberries. Refrigerate and chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease well and flour 2 round pans (8 x 11 1/2-inch).
Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Add eggs and beat 2 more minutes, scraping bowl constantly.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice with a fluffy white cooked icing.
Can be used as cupcakes or bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, onion and pecans. Form into a mound and make an indentation on top. Spread preserves all over the top, inside indentation. Serve with crackers of any kind. (This can be placed in a mold. When firm, turn out on a dish and put the preserves in the hole in the center.)

title: orange salad
directions: Crush crackers.
Add butter and sugar and layer in bottom of bowl for crust.
Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and frozen orange juice.
Fold in oranges.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
May be served frozen.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: In saucepan (1-quart), stir until hot the catsup, sugar and water.
Taste; add more sugar, if necessary, should be sweet. Score hot dogs (make several slits in each) and place in 7 x 9-inch pan.
Pour sauce over them and bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Turn hot dogs in sauce at least once.

title: flaky pastry
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour and salt; with pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in shortening.
Quickly sprinkle ice water 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing lightly until flour is mixed in. Shape pastry into ball; flatten to 1-inch thickness.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls(2 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in food processor and pulse until the texture of coarse meal.
Blend well the next three ingredients and add slowly to the processor while running.
Process about 30 seconds.
It should make a nice little dough ball.
Put dough in a greased bowl and let rise until double in volume.
Roll out on a lightly floured board to just the right size of rectangle 1/4 inch thick and smear with the softened margarine.
Sprinkle on a generous sprinkling of the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Roll up into a log and slice into about 24 slices (endwise).
Placed in 2 greased glass baking dishes and let rise until double.
This is the crucial time; they must rise a lot to be nice and fluffy.
Bake about 15 minutes or until barely golden brown.
Remove from oven and immediately brush generously with yummy thick glaze made from the powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat the eggs together with the sugar until light and well blended. Add the oil, continuing to beat.
Sift and stir the dry ingredients together and thoroughly beat them into the egg mixture. Add the pumpkin, mixing well again.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes. Turn out on a rack to cool. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: flavored sherbet
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup skim milk.
Heat evaporated milk with the sugar.
Add the softened jello and stir until dissolved. Cool.
Slowly add the lemon peel and juice to the cooled gelatin mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into ice cube trays and place in the freezer.
When mixture is mushy, remove and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Return to freezer until firm.
