Remove and put in a chilled bowl.
Beat until fluffy.
Re-freeze and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add the nuts and apples to sugar mixture.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Wash clams in 3 cups water.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Cut the hard part of the clam from the soft part.
Finely chop the hard parts.

title: dockside salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain well.
Combine spaghetti, peppers and onion.
Add dressing and toss to coat.
Sprinkle generously with paprika; stir well.
Add more paprika to give mixture a red color. Stir again.
Cover; refrigerate for 4 hours or longer, stirring once or twice.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: squash ala fisher
directions: Fry bacon and remove.
Saute onion in drippings.
Add squash, zucchini and tomatoes.
Cook until just soft.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: skiggie
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in large cast-iron skillet. Drain excess grease.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper and simmer 15 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Cook until tender.
Cover while cooking this mixture.
This is a one-pan dinner.
Cook macaroni according to directions.
Add to pan and mix thoroughly.
Serve while still hot.

title: s.o.s. hamburger
directions: Braise hamburger in roaster in oven.
Use enough water to leave broth to make gravy.
Cook until meat is done.
Stir and blend in 1 recipe roux.
Stir and blend in Pet milk, salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Over medium heat, saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add cream cheese and milk; stir over low heat until the cheese is melted.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water, add to cream cheese mixture.
Stir in broccoli, lemon juice, salt and pepper; heat thoroughly.
Top each serving with toasted almonds.

title: nana's orange-garlic roast pork
directions: Rinse the pork and dry it.
Mix together the salt, garlic, thyme and bay leaf.
Rub the mixture into the pork.
In a bowl, mix together the orange juice, vinegar and oil.
Place pork in container and pour liquid mixture over it.
Let stand 24 hours in the refrigerator, basting several times.
Roast on spit 30 minutes a pound.

title: cheezy broccoli casserole
directions: Place unopened packages of broccoli on end in microwave oven. Microwave
on High 4 to 5 minutes, turning over after 2 minutes; set aside.
In 3 quart casserole, combine rice, soup, milk, Cheez Whiz,
salt and pepper.
Microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes.
Cheese should
melt
and blend.
To cheese mixture, add
onion,
celery, water chestnuts and broccoli.
Stir thoroughly.
Divide into 2 lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch dishes. Microwave at
High
12 to 14 minutes.
Rotate and stir after 5 minutes.
Let
stand
5 minutes before serving.
This makes a large casserole.
Can be divided and frozen.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save 1 cup juice.
Drain all other fruits. Mix instant pudding with pineapple juice.
Mix all fruits except bananas and pour pudding mixture over fruit and stir. Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add bananas, sliced, and fold into fruit mixture.

title: huff 'n puffs
directions: Mix batter of flour, beer, cooking oil and salt.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 to 2 hours.
Beat egg white until stiff and fold into batter mixture.
Cut Vienna sausages into thirds.
Dip pieces into batter and fry in deep fat at 400° until batter is golden brown.
Serve hot.
Cut hot dogs into mouth sized pieces. Cut shrimp as desired.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in mixing bowl and set aside. Saute ground beef; drain and set aside.
In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, pour half of cornmeal mixture.
Sprinkle with ground beef, onions, jalapeno peppers, then cheese.
Pour remaining cornmeal mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: 125 year old walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat. Mix 1/2 flour with nuts and other half of flour with baking powder.
Mix in alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in a large greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325 degrees. Do not open oven for the first hour.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Layer ribs in a casserole dish.
Mix ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cook in slow oven at 325° for 3 1/2 hours or 7 hours in crock-pot.

title: guilt-free low-fat pasta salad
directions: Boil macaroni and rinse with cold water.
Slice tomatoes into small chunks.
Cut green peppers into small chunks.
Slice celery sticks in half down stalk and dice.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and chill for 1/2 hour and serve.
Makes approximately 8 servings (2 ounces).
Contains approximately 1.5 g fat per serving.

title: spanish chicken casserole
directions: Heat soup, tomatoes and Velveeta cheese until cheese is melted. Cook, drain and dice chicken breasts. Layer chips, chicken and cheese mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan. Make at least 2 layers. Top with shredded cheese. Heat in oven at 350° until cheese melts on top.

title: coconut-pineapple chess pie
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt into a bowl; mix well.
Add eggs, water, pineapple and coconut.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven until pie begins to brown.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake until firm (approximately 30 minutes).

title: plaza 3 steak soup
directions: Melt margarine, whisk in flour.
Stir in water.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add meat and bring to boil.
Add celery, onion, carrots, vegetables, tomatoes, Accent, B-V and pepper. Bring to boil and simmer 4 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients all together; spray dish with Pam. Put mixture in dish.
Crush Ritz crackers; sprinkle over top. Melt margarine and pour over Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: date roll-ups
directions: Stuff each pitted date with a pecan half.
Roll in brown sugar. Cut bacon slices into 4 pieces each.
Wrap 1 piece bacon around each stuffed date; secure with a toothpick.
Broil until bacon is crisp.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Melt
oleo
in	a 2 quart baking dish.	Sift together 1 cup sugar,
flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and stir until mixed.
Pour
over	butter	in
the baking dish; do not stir. Combine
peaches
and 1 cup sugar and spoon over batter in baking dish; do not stir.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour or less.

title: crustless savory quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Beat in cream cheese, cottage cheese and butter until almost smooth.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in egg mixture until thoroughly blended.
Beat in milk.
Pour into prepared pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese and meat or shellfish.
Sprinkle with green onions and mushrooms.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool slightly before eating.

title: cream cheese cake squares
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Gradually add powdered sugar, beating well.
Stir in vanilla. Pour mixture over first layer, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Yield:
About 4 dozen.

title: grits and cheese
directions: Cook grits in 6 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt.
When thickened, remove from heat and stir in cheese, margarine, Tabasco sauce, eggs and ham.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour, until cheese is melted and top is slightly browned.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: While rice is cooking, pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Brown meat in butter in a large skillet.
Add garlic and broth; cover and let simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and green peppers; cover and cook 5 more minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce; stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring, until clear and thickened (about 2 minutes).
Add tomatoes and mushrooms.
Stir gently.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Use plastic forms from craft store for making Reese's peanut butter cups or bonbon cups.

title: nadine's tater tot casserole
directions: Place
Tater
Tots
in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes at 400°.
Grate and combine cheeses.
Mix 1 cup cheese with the cream of celery soup and milk.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the following order:
Tater Tots (already in
pan), browned hamburger, broccoli, 1/2 can of French fried onions
and cheese and celery soup mixture.
Bake, covered at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover; top with 1 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 to 3 more minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: green bean and sausage soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Cook and stir onion in reserved drippings until tender.
Add carrots, potato, parsley, marjoram (if using), pepper and water.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add sausage, beans and reserved bacon.
Cook until well heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: boiled cookies
directions: In a saucepan on medium-high heat, mix first 5 ingredients. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add oatmeal and peanut butter. Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: brownie pies
directions: Mix melted margarine with cocoa.
Add sugar, salt and flour. Add beaten eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and coconut. Pour into 3 pie shells.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Best cooked on bottom rack of oven.

title: orange flavored biscotti
directions: Melt Crisco and margarine (cool).
Beat eggs and sugar, juices and cooled shortening.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder as needed to be workable without being too sticky.
Roll and cut into various shapes.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost if desired.

title: potato sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
In a large casserole, layer soup, potatoes and sausage. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and melt in oven.

title: hidden valley buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients (melted butter, pepper sauce and vinegar).
Dip chicken into sauce.
Put into a baking dish or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 package dry dressing mix.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes or until browned.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken a la mark
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash and trim fat from chicken breasts. Melt butter or margarine.
Pour bread crumbs into bowl.
Dip chicken into margarine and then coat with crumbs.
Place coated breasts into foil lined pan.
Bake for 40 minutes; broil for 5 minutes.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Fry the bacon and onion together.
Some of the grease may be drained, if you prefer.
Dilute both cans of potato soup with 1/2 cup of water and 1/2 cup milk.
Add the bacon and onion; stir and then add milk and cheese.
Stir until the cheese is melted.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Drain pineapple well; save juice. Add sugar, egg yolks and flour to pineapple juice and cook until it spins a thread. Add pineapple to juice mixture; cool completely. Spread on layers and stack. Cover with Seven-Minute Frosting.

title: cottage pie
directions: Boil potatoes; drain.
Mash with milk and seasonings.
Fry onion in oil until soft.
Add beef, carrot, celery and stock.
Cook 45 minutes.
Transfer to ovenproof dish.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Top with sharp Cheddar cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reba's vegetable medley
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer covered 15 minutes.
Put in serving dish; sprinkle with bacon bits.
Makes 4 servings.

title: flop cake
directions: Melt butter
in
pan.
Stir
in cake mix and 1 egg. Mix with mixer
cream
cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs and pour over cake mix mixture. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: "fresh" peach pie
directions: Mix oil, salt, sugar, milk and flour together with an electric mixer.
Press into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven; cool.
Mix sugar, water, cornstarch and dried jello in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Stir in 6 sliced peaches.
Pour into pie shell.
Cool completely.
Serve with whipped cream.
Can be made with strawberry jello and fresh strawberries.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9x13 baking dish.
Combine hot cooked spaghetti with butter, stir until butter melts and coats spaghetti.
Add 1/2 c. Parmesan cheese, stir to coat. Arrange spaghetti in an even layer in baking dish.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with 1/4 c. Parmesan cheese. Brown ground beef and drain; add pasta sauce and heat until bubbly.
Spoon over cheeses.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and remaining Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes. Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more or until cheese is lightly browned.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves six.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet lined with waxed paper; sprinkle chopped nuts on top (optional).
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar; peel paper off.
Roll and leave until cool.

title: orange cookie(pulitska)
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in oleo then add yolks, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix in orange juice and rind.
It will be a very soft dough.
Spoon out 1/3 of dough on a well floured board.
Pat dough down 1/2 inch thick.
Cut out circles 2 inches in diameter.
Put on cookie sheet.
Beat egg whites with fork and brush the top of cookie.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 350° for 8 mins.
Soft and puffy.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and cornflakes. Put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cornflakes on top. Dot with butter. Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: You can use red or green cherries.
Mix all together and chill before serving.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Crumble angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make lemon pudding as directed on box and pour over cake.
Add a layer of coconut.
Add a layer of Cool Whip.
Add a layer of coconut. Refrigerate for several hours, until set.

title: easy vegetarian enchiladas
directions: Tear 6 of the tortillas and spread on the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, then form meat balls. Put meat balls in 9 x 12 x 2 inch baking pan or any pan close to that size. A deep iron skillet works good. Pour one family size can of tomato sauce over meat balls. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: german potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes and cook until done.
Peel off jackets.
Dice potatoes, celery, onion and eggs.
Put in bowl and set aside.
In separate bowl, mix the following ingredients: eggs, cider vinegar, sugar, water, dry mustard and salt.

title: pound cake(never fail)
directions: Have margarine at room temperature.
Mix sugar and margarine; add eggs one at a time.
Add whipping cream (not whipped) alternately with flour.
Add lemon flavoring.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: ohio buckeyes
directions: Melt together over low heat the butter and peanut butter. Remove from heat and add sugar gradually.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on waxed paper and set in fridge for 1 hour.
Melt chocolate in double boiler and dip peanut butter balls into chocolate, partially exposing peanut butter to resemble the look of a buckeye.
Set back on waxed paper and put in freezer to harden.
Once hardened place in containers and refreeze until needed.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread mustard on top of loaf.
Bake for 2 hours.

title: sweet potatoes cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar and cream.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sweet potatoes and mix well.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture alternately with milk. Add nuts and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Can be served plain or with a cream cheese icing.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Let cream cheese get soft and cream together with the taco mix.
Spread shredded lettuce on a plate.
Top with salsa, cream cheese mix.
Add chopped tomatoes to this and top the whole thing off with Cheddar cheese.
Serve with favorite chip.
Double recipe for a crowd.

title: hand lotion
directions: Wal-Mart has the Unibase most of the time (ask in the Pharmacy).
Watch the glycerin.
If it has "synthetic" under the name, don't buy it.
It doesn't work as well.

title: dinette cake
directions: Beat in large mixing bowl on low speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: surprise dessert
directions: Combine butter, sugar, oatmeal and coconut.
Spread on cookie sheet and brown lightly in moderate oven.
Watch carefully and stir occasionally as it will burn easily.
Place a jar of caramel sauce in pan of hot water to soften.
When mixture is cool enough to handle, spread 3/4 of it over a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts over mixture and drizzle caramel sauce over nuts.
Have ice cream soft enough to spread out in your dish.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth with peppers and onion until spaghetti is done.
Drain excess liquid.
Add soup, cheese, chopped eggs and chicken.
Put ingredients in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: idiot rolls
directions: Heat in pan until melted the margarine and shortening.
Add 1 cup water.
Cool.
Dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water. Mix eggs, 1 cup cold water and sugar.
Combine all ingredients in bowl. Stir in sifted flour, cover and place in refrigerator. About 3 hours before you need them, take amount needed out. Roll into balls and put into greased pans.
Let rise 3 hours. Bake 7 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pie crust
directions: Place ingredients in pie plate and stir to make a ball.
Now use the bowl of a large spoon or the palm of your hand to shape your pie crust.
Makes 1 large pie crust.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix all the other ingredients together; cook until it becomes a creamed mixture, then pour over cooked macaroni.
Take bread, cut up into pieces, and put into melted butter, then pour over macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add brown sugar and salt.
Fold in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° until light brown.

title: butter goo cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix vanilla, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over first layer. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, eggs and sugar.
Add flour.
Blend all dry ingredients; stir in.
Roll into balls
the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon; place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookies puff at first, then flatten.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes.
Put stick of oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan and melt.
Mix soup, sour cream, milk and onion.
Put half of potatoes in pan and pour half of soup mixture over top. Then add half of cheese; repeat layers.
Top with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix in ungreased pan, first 5 ingredients.
Make 3 wells in blended dry ingredients.
In each one, add vanilla, vinegar and cooking oil separately.
Cover with water and mix well with fork. Scrape sides and bake.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: arroz amarillo con pollo (rice and chicken)
directions: In a saucepan, bring 2 1/2 cups water to a boil; add a tablespoon oil and 2 tablespoon butter or margarine and rice. Stir for 1 minute; cover pan tightly, reduce to a simmer.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: fried corn
directions: Shuck and silk corn.
In a large bowl, cut corn off the cob, slicing off the top of the kernels.
Scrape the cob to the milky juice.
Melt some butter in a nonstick skillet; pour in corn.
Add enough milk or water to make it soupy.
Add butter and salt.
Cook on medium heat, stirring often.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat, seasoning and chopped onion.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Spread meat in bottom of casserole.
Spread beans on top. Spread tomato soup over that.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven, put a layer of tortillas on the bottom (don't skimp on the tortilla layers; each layer needs to cover the
whole surface).
Sprinkle
with
hamburger
and
cheese. Spoon over some sauce.
Repeat process, but leave room at the top of the Dutch oven.
Bake at 325° or until you can't stand it anymore.

title: fabulous fruit tart
directions: *Sliced bananas, plums or blueberries may be substituted.

title: fruit fondue
directions: Combine & chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: cabbage crunch salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Stir in dressing; add the noodles.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: creamy apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer rice and chicken.
Then top with soups.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Cook chicken in butter and add next 3 ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Add broth, tomatoes, corn, picante sauce and cumin. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 20-30 minutes, covered.

title: microwave potatoes, or "sure, stay for dinner!"
directions: Slice potato thin.
Slice onion.
In bottom of microwave dish, put butter or margarine.
Place potato and onion on top of butter. Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir.
Continue microwaving until done.

title: lee's favorite sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients to flour and sift. Alternate adding eggs and flour mixture to butter mixture.
Add sour cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: grandma's chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add all ingredients and simmer at least 1 hour.

title: onion clam dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Good with Bugles and Fritos!

title: knock me cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake mix as directed.
Poke holes in hot cake.
Spread Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Add caramel topping. Cool cake.
Add Heath bars (5 only).
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle 1 crushed Heath bar on top.
Serve cold.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add whole cranberry sauce and stir until blended. Chill until partially thickened. Add pecans and drained crushed pineapple. For a richer red color, add a drop or two of red food coloring. Pour into a lightly greased square pan or dish. Chill until firm. Blend mayonnaise with cream cheese and serve with salad.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Cream shortening at medium speed of an electric mixer; gradually add the sugar, beating well.
Add the eggs, zucchini and water; mix thoroughly.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices; add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Stir in pecans. Spoon batter into an 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan, greased only on bottom.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour in small loaf pan.

title: zucchini pie
directions: In a frying pan, combine first three ingredients and cook for 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, salt, pepper and 1/4 teaspoon of basil, oregano and garlic powder.
Add shredded Mozzarella cheese to egg mixture, then add zucchini mixture.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Marinate chicken over night or for two hours before cooking. Perfect for grilling of in the
oven.

title: challah
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl. Add sugar, salt, oil, eggs and approximately 6 cups flour. Beat thoroughly. Add more flour. Turn onto floured surface and knead adding more flour as needed. Place in greased covered bowl until tripled or 1 1/2 hours. Divide into thirds.
Divide each third again into thirds and shape into 3 ropes.
Braid ropes together. Let rise on cookie sheets until triple. Brush with egg wash and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or golden brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and spices in large pot.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients, except beans, and cook 1 hour.
Add beans and heat through.
Serve with shredded Longhorn cheese and crushed corn chips.

title: potato soup
directions: In a pan, put potatoes, onion, carrot and celery.
Cover with enough water to cook until potatoes are soft, then add 3 cups of milk and margarine, salt and pepper to taste.
Let cook about 5 minutes longer.

title: chex mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250. Melt margarine in a large roasting style pan. Stir in all of the worcestershire sauce and salts.
Add ingredients exactly in this order to make certain everything gets coated without getting moist.
Add peanuts, stir thoroughly to coat.
Add pretzels, stir to coat.
Add Corn Chex, stir. Add Rice Chex. Stir altogether. Add Cheerios and stir. Bake for an hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Lay flat on towels over newspaper to dry.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soups, broth and green chilies.
Dip shells in mixture and set aside.
Put chicken and cheeses in center of tortillas and roll up.
Place in baking dish.
Pour remaining soup over enchiladas and top with remaining cheese.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Butter cake pan and pour in mixture; spoon pie filling 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly over each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix well.
Put in greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: frozen cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening (about 2 minutes). Add eggs. Dissolve soda in 1/3 cup of hot water.
Add to mixture and beat. Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add.
Add nut meats. Divide into 4 or 5 rolls. Wrap in wax paper and either chill overnight or freeze (keeps well in freezer). Slice and bake at 350°.
Coconut or chocolate chips may be added.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil, milk and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda; add to first mixture. Mix by hand only!
No mixer!
Add hot water and blend.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Frost when cooled.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, salad oil, vinegar and cold water in saucepan.
Cook until boiling and sugar dissolves.
Pour over cabbage and green pepper.
Chill several hours, stirring occasionally.

title: marinated beans
directions: Marinate overnight.
Toss a few times.
Nice served cold with meal.

title: potato tortilla
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Rinse and pat dry.
Chop onions in small pieces.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes, placing in a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt, thyme leaves and garlic.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box, pour 1/2 batter into a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with butter and milk, pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour rest of cake batter on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: wesson oil cake
directions: Sift first five ingredients together into a 9 x 13-inch pan and make 3 holes.
In the first hole, put oil, in the second hole the vinegar and in the third hole the vanilla.
Pour 2 cups cold water over the whole cake and mix with a fork until well mixed. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until spins thread or forms hard ball in cold water.
Add peanuts and salt.
Stir and cook until light golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and soda. Stir well and pour on well-greased cookie sheet.
Will be more brittle if not spread.
Just let run out on pan.
Break when cold.

title: streusel-topped sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover 35 to 40 minutes or until tender. Drain and let cool. Peel and mash potatoes.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice and next 6 ingredients.
Stir well and set aside.

title: baked prunes
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine the applesauce, apple juice, lemon juice, vanilla, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Stir in apricots, prunes, figs and pear.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 4.

title: mrs. reagan's cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar. Add unbeaten egg, lemon and orange extracts, orange rind and juice. Mix well.
Blend with dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in nuts. Chill 1 to 2 hours or until needed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into sugar and roll to coat.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1/2 minute and remove fast to waxed paper.
(Scrape crumbs from pan, cover pan with wet cloth to clean.)
Prepare 2nd sheet of cookies while 1st bakes.
Rotate pans until finished; 3 tins are best.

title: chicken spinach pinwheels
directions: In a medium bowl, combine spinach, egg, cheese, pimento and 1 tablespoon mustard.
Spread mixture on each chicken breast and roll.
Fasten with toothpick.
Place rolls in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Drizzle rolls with butter.
Bake 40 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: crab meat and cream cheese
directions: Place cream cheese on platter.
Put crab meat on top and pour cocktail sauce over.
Surround with crackers.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Melt wax in double boiler.
Add Hershey bars and chocolate chips.
Melt and set aside.
Mix together peanut butter and powdered sugar and add Rice Krispies.
Form into balls and dip into chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper.

title: triple layer cookie bar
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs.
Top with coconut then pour milk over it.
Bake 25 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Spread over coconut.
Let cool 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: homemade cream of chicken soup
directions: In microwave, boil 1 cup water with 1 tablespoon soup base until dissolved.
Set aside.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium-high heat until sizzling.
Using a wire whisk, add flour and briskly stir.
Brown flour in butter.
Add salt and pepper as you continue to stir.
Add the soup base and water mixture along with the milk and onion.
Continue to whisk until thickened.
You may add more soup base to the finished produce to taste by dissolving it in a few tablespoons of water and stirring into finished soup.
Makes about 16 ounces of soup.

title: cream sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until very light and creamy.
Add cold water and sugar.
Add flour and cornstarch, sift together.
Whip the whites of eggs stiff; fold in.
Add flavoring or juice.
Bake in 9-inch tube pan in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Cook sugar, flour, egg and juice until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool; fold in whipped cream.
Spread over congealed salad; sprinkle with cheese and chill.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: goofy cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and baking powder in an ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Make three holes in dry ingredients. Put 1 tablespoon vinegar in one hole, 1/3 cup oil in second hole and 1 teaspoon vanilla in third hole.
Pour in 1 cup of cold water and mix until smooth. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; add soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in hash browns.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt other stick of butter; add corn flakes and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand while mixing other dry ingredients.
Mix soda, flour and salt.
Beat eggs slightly and add oil and vanilla.
Add egg mixture and apple mixture alternately to dry ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x 15-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
It is best while it's still warm.
Keep covered to make sure it doesn't dry out.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Mix well.
Stir and cook over medium heat until thickened (12 minutes); remove. Stir in rest of ingredients.
Beat until spreading consistency. Frost with seven minute frosting or caramel frosting.
This freezes well.

title: baked brie
directions: Roll crescent dough flat like pastry.
Reserve about 1/3 for decoration, if desired.
Wrap Brie wedge completely in dough and seal.
Place in baking dish with sealed side on bottom.
Use reserved dough for cutting decorations to place on top (I cut small leaves).
Brush with lightly beaten egg white.
Bake at 350° until browned and bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: light cornmeal muffins
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg substitute, yogurt and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon mixture into muffin pans coated with vegetable cooking spray, filling three-fourths full.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove muffins from pans immediately.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen (96 calories per muffin).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put butter and onion in pan and cook.
Add rest of ingredients (except Cheez Whiz) and cook 10 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and mix. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
May top with bread crumbs or Ritz cracker crumbs, if desired.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to boil in microwave.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add soda and stir in real well.
Put popped corn in paper bag and pour syrup mixture over it; shake well.
Roll up top of bag and put in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out and shake again.
Cook another 1 1/2 minutes, then pour on cookie sheet to cool.
Yum!

title: mallow topped sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except marshmallows, until well blended.
Spoon into a 1-quart casserole.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake for 20 minutes until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes a very stiff batter. Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together.
Add rest.
Chill and serve.

title: salmon patties
directions: Crush 1 tube of saltine crackers on wax paper and set aside. Mix in bowl, salon (drained), 1 tube of crushed crackers, eggs (beaten), 1 (8 ounce) package Mozzarella cheese or less and about 1/4 cup of catsup (you can guess).
Make into palm-size patties and press both sides into the crushed saltines on wax paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish and microwave 10 to 15 minutes.

title: brer rabbit molasses gingerbread cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar and egg.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add alternately with molasses and hot water.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350° in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: mexican salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle avocado with lemon juice.
Fry ground beef, breaking it apart as it cooks. Drain thoroughly on paper towel and set aside.
Combine lettuce in salad bowl with ingredients through cheese.
Crumble taco chips a bit and add to salad, along with ground beef and add salad dressing to taste.
Toss.
Garnish with tomatoes and eggs.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon lush
directions: 1st Layer:
Combine flour and margarine with pastry blender until crumbly.
Add pecans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely before adding 2nd layer.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saute chicken cutlets (cut into medium pieces).
In another pan, fry peppers which are cut in pieces.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes. Place them in a dish.
In the same pan, cook celery and onion until tender.
You can add mushrooms if using fresh ones (cut into slices).
Season to taste.
Then combine vegetables and chicken. Add your sauce and cook 1 hour.

title: crab pasta salad
directions: Chop green onions and tomato.
Wash and chop uncooked broccoli, crab delights and rotini primavera.
Follow cooking directions on package.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix and pour into shallow pan.
After it sets up, cut into squares to serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to boil 3 minutes and then add 2 Tbsp. peanut butter, 1 tsp. vanilla, and 3 c. oats.

title: applesauce
directions: Cut and core apples.
Quarter and drop in a pan with 1/2 teaspoon of water.
Let cook until soft.
Pour into sifter and turn until apples are through.
Add a pinch of cinnamon.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift flour and confectioners sugar (I just squiggle around) into bowl.
Blend in butter until well mixed.
Pat evenly into bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hours at 325°.

title: canned fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit (all but bananas) and add 1 instant lemon pie filling.
Add bananas shortly before serving.
Pie filling thickens the fruit juices slightly as it chills.
Stores well in the refrigerator for several days.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Add all dry ingredients and blend well.
Add nuts, crushed (optional).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Fill loaf pans 3/4 full.

title: cinnamon fruit biscuit crunchies
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each biscuit into butter and then in sugar mixture.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Make a deep thumbprint in center of each roll.
Fill with 1 teaspoon preserves.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Chop bacon; place in pressure cooker and cook until almost brown, then drain almost all fat.
Add ground beef and cook until no longer pink.
Add onion, celery, carrots, cabbage, tomatoes and juice, 2 bouillon cubes, drained kidney beans, green peas, corn and raw rice.
Add 3 cups water (if using 5-quart cooker, add all water), garlic, salt and pepper and stir.
Bring pressure to 15 pounds and cook 15 minutes.
Let pressure return to normal and remove cover.
Add 1 cup or more water and heat.
Serve.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine butter, two cups of flour and 1 cup of confectioners sugar.
Pat into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat together eggs, sugar, baking powder, 4 tablespoons flour and lemon juice.
Pour over baked crust and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: copper pennies-carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots, cook until just tender.
Drain.
Mix onions, green pepper, sugar, salad oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to carrots.
Chill.

title: pay day bars
directions: Spread half the jar of peanuts over the bottom of 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan, buttered.
Melt the butter and peanut butter chips over medium heat.
When blended, add sweetened condensed milk. When blended, add miniature marshmallows.
Mix until marshmallows start to soften.
Remove from heat and pour mixture over the peanuts in the pan; spread evenly.
Top with remaining peanuts and pat them down gently.
Can be refrigerated.

title: rich pudding
directions: Mix pudding
according
to
package.
Fold in Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Pour over alternate layers of bananas and wafers. Chill and serve.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix together and make into balls.
Put in 9 x 13 inch pan or pans.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients; blend until moistened. Beat 2 minutes. Fill muffin cups 1/2 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°. Makes 24.

title: guacamole
directions: Avocados should be seeded, peeled and cut up in a blender container or food processor bowl. Combine avocados, onion, peppers, garlic, lime juice and salt.
Cover and blend or process until nearly smooth, stopping and scraping sides as necessary. Transfer mixture to a bowl. Cover with plastic directly touching the surface to prevent darkening.
Chill for up to 24 hours.

title: cheese wafers
directions: You can omit pepper if you choose and add a couple drops of hot sauce and 2 shakes of Worcestershire sauce.
Cream butter and cheese until light and fluffy.
Add salt, red pepper or hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well.
Add flour, gradually, and then add Rice Krispies.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Mix margarine, onion and flour in a saucepan.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thick.
Add cheese and half of cracker crumbs.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash sweet potatoes.
Add eggs, white sugar, melted margarine and vanilla.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/4 cup margarine and pecans.
Sprinkle over top of sweet potatoes.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
